1
00:00:48,530 --> 00:00:53,630
{\fs30}国家宝藏2：夺宝秘笈

2
00:00:55,130 --> 00:00:58,130
华盛顿  1865年4月14日

3
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,530
南北战争结束后第五天

4
00:01:15,890 --> 00:01:17,790
他在里面
{\fs10}He's in the other room.

5
00:01:25,740 --> 00:01:28,400
- 你是托马斯・盖茨？ - 对
{\fs10}- Are you Thomas Gates？ - Yes.

6
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:32,270
有些东西想让你看看
{\fs10}We got something that we'd like you to take a look at.

7
00:01:32,610 --> 00:01:35,640
听说你很会解谜
{\fs10}I hear you're quite good with puzzles and riddles.

8
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:40,510
- 是条加密的信息 - 这是普莱费厄密码
{\fs10}- It's a coded message. - It's a Playfair cipher.

9
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:44,520
- 普莱费厄密码？ - 你能解码吗？
{\fs10}- Playfair cipher？ - Can you decode it？

10
00:01:44,590 --> 00:01:47,080
解那种密码得要有密钥
{\fs10}Cipher's impossible to decode without the key.

11
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:51,320
- 密钥是什么意思？ - 一个关键字句
{\fs10}- What do you mean by "a key"？ - A keyword or phrase.

12
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:54,760
我相信你需要东西的就在这里
{\fs10}I believe what you need is right there.

13
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,760
凡人皆要还之债！

14
00:01:54,830 --> 00:01:56,820
这得花点时间
{\fs10}It'll take some time.

15
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:02,900
走吧，我拿日记，待会再跟你会合
{\fs10}Go on. I'll take your diary. I'll meet up with you later.

16
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,590
只要算好距离，保准你能正中靶心{\fs12}(舞台上正表演《我们的美国表弟》)
{\fs10}…calculate the distance and you're sure to hit the mark

17
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:30,930
这样不仅打手枪很准，打炮也很准哦
{\fs10}in about most things as well as shootin'.

18
00:02:33,370 --> 00:02:37,810
…我要将它浇你身，就像狗头浇上粪
{\fs10}…ready to pour out all over you like apple sass over roast pork.

19
00:02:43,150 --> 00:02:46,120
我得当心点，不能把手上的东西 泼到可怜的德・布茨老爷身上
{\fs10}I'll take care not to give up my hold on poor De Boots

20
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:48,750
要泼也得等了解美国人之后再泼
{\fs10}till I am quite sure of the American.

21
00:02:48,820 --> 00:02:53,590
嗯，我女儿真乖
{\fs10}Ah, that's my own girl.

22
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:55,560
奥古斯塔，亲爱的，去你房间怎么样
{\fs10}Augusta, dear, to your room.

23
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:04,000
展示一下你的内在美吧，我的好姑娘 特别是那片幽深的草场，令人心荡漾
{\fs10}…to turn you inside out, old gal, you sockdologizing old man-trap.

24
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:15,680
【拉丁语】打倒专制君主！
{\fs10}Sic semper tyrannis！

25
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,860
神殿…
{\fs10}Temples.

26
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:36,730
黄金…
{\fs10}Gold.

27
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:40,270
锡沃拉？这是张藏宝图！
{\fs10}Cibola？ This is a treasure map.

28
00:03:42,070 --> 00:03:46,100
KGC？你是金环骑士会成员！叛国贼！
{\fs10}KGC？ You're Knights of the Golden Circle. You're a traitor.

29
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:48,200
你们都是叛国贼
{\fs10}You're all traitors.

30
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:53,980
- 林肯总统被刺了！ - 出去！全都出去！
{\fs10}- President Lincoln's been shot！ - Everybody, out！ All of you！

31
00:03:54,050 --> 00:03:55,990
杀手仍然在逃
{\fs10}Killer's on the loose！

32
00:03:58,490 --> 00:04:02,480
马上破译密文，本人感激不尽
{\fs10}I'd much appreciate it if you'd finish deciphering that code now.

33
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:10,430
- 爸爸！ - 战争结束了！
{\fs10}- Dad！ - The war is over.

34
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:13,800
不！
{\fs10}No！

35
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:20,670
- 不要 - 别
{\fs10}- No！ - No！

36
00:04:26,020 --> 00:04:27,750
你错了
{\fs10}You're wrong about that.

37
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:31,450
战争才刚开始
{\fs10}The war has only just begun！

38
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:39,630
查尔斯，“凡人皆要还之债…”
{\fs10}Charles. The debt that all men… men pay.

39
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:42,500
凡人皆要还之…
{\fs10}The debt that all men p…

40
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,860
爸！不要死！
{\fs10}Dad！ No, please！

41
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:54,210
别死，这不公平
{\fs10}Come back. It's not fair.

42
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,480
救命！来人，救命啊！
{\fs10}Help！ Somebody help, please！

43
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,970
所以，我在此重述
{\fs10}So recapping:

44
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:05,080
金环骑士会是一个南方的极端团体
{\fs10}The Knights of the Golden Circle was a Southern extremist group,

45
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:08,280
他们在北方活动，暗中破坏联邦政府
{\fs10}operating in the north to subvert Union forces.

46
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:12,920
如果那几页著名的布斯日记没被托马斯烧毁
{\fs10}Had Thomas not burned the legendary missing pages from the Booth diary,

47
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,930
杀手可能早已找到大批黄金宝藏
{\fs10}the killers may have found a vast treasure of gold,

48
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,940
而联邦政府也可能输掉南北战争
{\fs10}and the Union may well have lost the Civil War.

49
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,370
谢谢大家
{\fs10}Thank you.

50
00:05:23,810 --> 00:05:26,610
感谢本和帕特里克・盖茨两位…
{\fs10}I'd like to thank Ben and Patrick Gates.

51
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,670
谢谢
{\fs10}Thank you.

52
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:34,010
为我们讲述了一个精彩绝伦的传奇 以及托马斯・盖茨这位平民英雄
{\fs10}And say what a wonderful addition Thomas Gates is to our civilian heroes exhibit.

53
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:35,070
谢谢大家
{\fs10}Thank you.

54
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,550
谢谢，尼克尔斯博士，我只希望我爷爷
{\fs10}Thank you, Dr. Nichols. I only wish my grandfather

55
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:41,850
今天也能到场参与盛会
{\fs10}had been here to see this wonderful day.

56
00:05:41,930 --> 00:05:44,450
抱歉，我有个问题想问
{\fs10}Excuse me. I have a question I'd like to ask.

57
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:47,330
你认为那页被焚毁的布斯日记上…
{\fs10}What do you think happened to that Booth diary page

58
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:50,300
- 究竟写了什么呢？ - 可能永远没法知道了
{\fs10}- that was pulled out of the fire？ - We may never know.

59
00:05:50,370 --> 00:05:51,800
可能没办法
{\fs10}Perhaps.

60
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:55,530
也可能有办法
{\fs10}Perhaps not.

61
00:05:55,610 --> 00:05:59,370
和你们一样，我的家族里也有位曾曾祖父
{\fs10}You see, I have one of those great-great-granddaddies, like you,

62
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:03,240
他名叫塞拉斯・威尔金森
{\fs10}way up in my family tree, name of Silas Wilkinson.

63
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:07,240
他曾说过一个林肯被刺当晚的故事
{\fs10}He used to tell a story about the night Lincoln was shot.

64
00:06:07,590 --> 00:06:09,280
依他的说法
{\fs10}As Silas tells it,

65
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:13,590
布斯当晚并没有找托马斯・盖茨 谈什么藏宝图的事
{\fs10}Booth didn't seek out Thomas Gates regarding the treasure map that night.

66
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,450
是托马斯召集聚会
{\fs10}It was Thomas who called the meeting.

67
00:06:16,530 --> 00:06:19,430
计划暗杀林肯
{\fs10}A meeting to plan the assassination of Lincoln.

68
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:21,990
- 太荒谬了 - 你说谎！
{\fs10}- How absurd. - That's a lie！

69
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:26,240
女士们先生们，请看…
{\fs10}Ladies and gentlemen, I present to you…

70
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:31,430
这张纸就是约翰・布斯日记中遗失的一页
{\fs10}…one of the missing pages from the infamous diary of John Wilkes Booth

71
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:36,210
上面有托马斯・盖茨的名字 和其他凶手的名字在一起
{\fs10}with the name Thomas Gates written on a list along with all the other killers.

72
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,810
- 这是拉丁文？ - 布斯曾学过拉丁文
{\fs10}- And Latin？ - Booth was a student of Latin.

73
00:06:42,890 --> 00:06:46,080
他射杀林肯后大喊 “Sic semper tyrannis”
{\fs10}He shouted, "Sic semper tyrannis" after he shot Lincoln.

74
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,680
- 打倒… - 打倒专制君主，我们知道
{\fs10}- "Thus always to… " - "Thus always to tyrants. " We know.

75
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:54,390
- 萨拉特，copiae？ - copiae意思是军需供应
{\fs10}- "Surratt, copiae"？ - Military supplies.

76
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:56,800
玛丽・萨拉特被控有罪并处以绞刑
{\fs10}Mary Surratt was convicted and hanged

77
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:59,770
罪名是为布斯提供步枪和瞄准镜
{\fs10}for supplying Booth with a rifle and field glasses.

78
00:07:03,610 --> 00:07:07,810
- 托马斯・盖茨，artifex - 意思是设计师
{\fs10}- "Thomas Gates, artifex. " - "Designer"

79
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:11,250
- 或者说策划者 - 我知道这字的意思
{\fs10}- or "mastermind. " - I know what it means.

80
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,580
一定是他策划暗杀的
{\fs10}He must have, uh, planned the assassination.

81
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:18,650
- 我明白了 - 也可能是策划别的事情
{\fs10}- I see. - Could mean mastermind of anything.

82
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,350
你看见没有？后面的内容被烧掉了
{\fs10}You see that？ Burned out right there.

83
00:07:23,090 --> 00:07:26,030
我知道，对你而言这事情很难接受
{\fs10}I can only imagine how difficult this must be for you.

84
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:28,900
- 请问，这位先生… - 威尔金森
{\fs10}- May I, Mr？ - Wilkinson.

85
00:07:28,970 --> 00:07:31,660
我来看看这页纸和布斯日记是否吻合
{\fs10}I'll see if this new page matches the Booth diary.

86
00:07:31,740 --> 00:07:34,900
这简直是侮辱，你说我的祖父是个骗子
{\fs10}This is an outrage. You're calling my grandfather a liar.

87
00:07:34,970 --> 00:07:38,530
你的意思是，我的曾曾祖父是个骗子
{\fs10}With respect, now you're calling my great-great-granddaddy a liar.

88
00:07:38,610 --> 00:07:41,810
没错，我就是这个意思 我所说的不是从什么历史书里查来的垃圾
{\fs10}Yes, sir, I am. This isn't some garbage from a history book.

89
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:44,250
而是我祖父亲口告诉我的
{\fs10}My grandfather told me this story himself.

90
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:47,750
- 他的眼睛告诉我那些都是真话 - 我很遗憾，先生，真的很遗憾
{\fs10}- I saw the truth of it in his eyes. - I'm sorry, sir. I truly am.

91
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,620
这纸还得接受全面检测，然后才能做定论
{\fs10}We'll test this thoroughly, Patrick, to authenticate it.

92
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,670
怎么可能…
{\fs10}It can't be.

93
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,870
总统府的地图
{\fs10}Maps to presidents' houses.

94
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:12,440
有钥匙却没有要开的锁
{\fs10}Keys to locks that don't exist.

95
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:16,640
这是为什么呢？我究竟在找什么？
{\fs10}What's the point？ What am I looking for？

96
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:20,180
证据，证据，证据…
{\fs10}Proof, proof, proof.

97
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:23,020
什么证据呢？
{\fs10}What proof？

98
00:08:33,690 --> 00:08:35,520
圣殿宝藏，作者 莱利・普尔

99
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:47,300
这本书是讲圣殿骑士宝藏的吗？
{\fs10}Oh, wow. Is this a book about the Templar treasure？

100
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:51,910
对，里面有讲到圣殿骑士的宝藏 但也有说到其它很多事
{\fs10}Yes, it is about the Templar treasure, but it's also about other things.

101
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:56,480
阴谋理论，民间传说… 及其它一些已被证实的神话
{\fs10}Conspiracy theories, urban legends and other myths that are true.

102
00:08:56,550 --> 00:09:00,010
- 作者是不是在这儿签名售书啊？ - 作者就是在下
{\fs10}- So the author's here signing copies？ - I'm the author.

103
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:02,490
- 你就是？ - 嗯，你看
{\fs10}- You are？ - Yeah. See, uh…

104
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:05,260
那里面有我的照片
{\fs10}There's a picture of me right there.

105
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:09,060
我认为那张拍的相当不错
{\fs10}I think it's a pretty good picture.

106
00:09:09,130 --> 00:09:12,430
我听说宝藏是那个 叫本杰明・盖茨的人发现的
{\fs10}I thought that guy, Benjamin Gates, found the treasure.

107
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:16,370
是本发现的没错，但我是他的搭档
{\fs10}Well, yes, Ben did, but I am the co-finder.

108
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:19,500
从没听说过
{\fs10}- Oh, I've never heard of you. - Oh！

109
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:27,280
我的天，你就是本・盖茨？
{\fs10}Oh, my gosh. Are you Ben Gates？

110
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:32,180
- 是的，我就是 - 你是不是有辆红色法拉利？
{\fs10}- Yes. Yes, I am. - Do you own a red Ferrari？

111
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:37,420
- 对，我有 - 嗯，它要被拖走了
{\fs10}- Yes, I do. - Well, it's being towed.

112
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:51,070
等等，那是我的车
{\fs10}Wait！ Wait！ That's my car！

113
00:09:58,020 --> 00:09:59,240
你的法拉利呢？
{\fs10}Where's the Ferrari？

114
00:10:00,590 --> 00:10:03,650
- 被国税局没收了 - 国税局？
{\fs10}- IRS impounded it. - The IRS？

115
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:08,320
说来滑稽，我的会计帮我
{\fs10}Funny story. My accountant set up a corporation

116
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:10,590
在一个虚构的岛上设立了一家公司
{\fs10}on an island that didn't exist

117
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:13,690
还告诉我富人们都是这么干的
{\fs10}and assured me that that's how rich people do it.

118
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:18,400
后来么，就有人来查我的账 还罚了一大笔钱，外加利息
{\fs10}Then I got audited and slapped with a huge fine plus interest.

119
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,360
知道五百万元要交多少税吗？
{\fs10}Wanna know what taxes are on five million dollars？

120
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,740
要交六百万元
{\fs10}Six million dollars.

121
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:27,600
我说完了
{\fs10}But enough about me.

122
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:30,040
你最近怎么样？
{\fs10}What's new with you？

123
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:34,980
女朋友把我赶出来了，我目前和我爸一起住
{\fs10}Well, my girlfriend kicked me out, I'm living with my dad,

124
00:10:35,050 --> 00:10:38,180
- 还有我的祖辈刺杀了林肯总统 - 不错
{\fs10}- my family killed President Lincoln. - All right.

125
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:41,090
我要你帮忙
{\fs10}I need your help.

126
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:44,390
不敢相信你竟然连自己家都要用闯的
{\fs10}I can't believe you have to break into your own house.

127
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:48,160
我得拿到阿比盖尔的工作证 这样就能查阅布斯的日记了
{\fs10}I need to get Abigail's ID. She has access to the Booth diary page.

128
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,360
为什么不直接找阿比盖尔帮忙？
{\fs10}Why don't you ask Abigail for her help？

129
00:10:50,430 --> 00:10:53,840
她把安防密码都改了，莱利 她现在连话都不想和我说
{\fs10}She changed the alarm code, Riley. She's not going to talk to me.

130
00:10:53,910 --> 00:10:54,960
好吧
{\fs10}All right.

131
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:59,500
我们有30秒时间来解除警报
{\fs10}We have 30 seconds after the alert starts to disable the alarm.

132
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:02,980
开始
{\fs10}Go.

133
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:11,780
或许我不该问，但你和她究竟怎么了？
{\fs10}I'll probably regret asking this, but what happened with you and Abigail？

134
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:15,620
我不知道…她最近总是说“那么”这个词
{\fs10}I don't know. I don't know. She started using the word "so" a lot.

135
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:17,090
“那么”？
{\fs10}"So？"

136
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:20,220
比如说“那么我的意见无关紧要咯”
{\fs10}Yeah, like, "So, I guess my opinion doesn't matter. "

137
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:24,200
“那么说你总比我高明咯” “那么我是形同虚设的咯”
{\fs10}"So, you seem to always know what's best. " "So, I guess I'm invisible. "

138
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:27,030
我已经从这儿搬走了，正在协商怎么分家具
{\fs10}Now I've moved out, we're dividing furniture…

139
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:28,920
Oh.

140
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:33,500
不能和女人一起住 尤其不能和换了安防密码的女人一起住
{\fs10}Women. Can't live with them, especially if they change the alarm codes.

141
00:11:33,950 --> 00:11:35,610
你25秒就搞定了
{\fs10}You did that in 25 seconds.

142
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,170
所以我总劝别人，还是养条狗好
{\fs10}That's why I tell people to get a dog.

143
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,750
- 找到了 - 好，我们走
{\fs10}- Got it. - All right, let's go.

144
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:51,850
那不是阿比盖尔的车
{\fs10}That's not Abigail's car.

145
00:11:54,430 --> 00:11:55,900
她在和人约会
{\fs10}She was on a date.

146
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:59,460
那个男的，不就是白宫的那家伙么
{\fs10}Isn't that that guy？ The White House guy？

147
00:11:59,570 --> 00:12:03,270
下周一是白宫复活节“滚彩蛋”大赛 如果你没什么…
{\fs10}The White House Easter Egg Roll is next Monday. Maybe if you're not…

148
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:04,300
这人挺怪的
{\fs10}He's weird！

149
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:07,040
如果孩子们没找到所有彩蛋怎么办？
{\fs10}What happens if kids don't find all the eggs？

150
00:12:07,110 --> 00:12:09,840
你上班在博物馆，回家还住博物馆？
{\fs10}Wow. You work in a museum, and you live in one.

151
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:11,180
差不多吧
{\fs10}Pretty much.

152
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:13,770
伶牙俐齿啊，她一定喜欢上他了
{\fs10}What clever repartee. She must like him.

153
00:12:13,850 --> 00:12:16,880
好吧，我带你参观一下这房子
{\fs10}All right, let me give you a tour of the house.

154
00:12:16,950 --> 00:12:19,480
- 好的 - 实际上这里是…
{\fs10}- OK. - That's actually kind of…

155
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,290
阿比盖尔
{\fs10}Oh, Abigail.

156
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:25,090
- 你到这儿来干嘛？ - 我只是来拿点东西
{\fs10}- What are you doing here？ - I just needed to get some things.

157
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,560
- 康纳，很高兴又见到你了 - 你好盖茨
{\fs10}- Connor, good to see you again. - Gates.

158
00:12:29,330 --> 00:12:30,860
你怎么进来的，本？
{\fs10}How did you get in, Ben？

159
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:36,470
莱利，给我出来
{\fs10}Riley！ Come out here！

160
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,540
什么事？
{\fs10}What？

161
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:46,750
嘿，你怎么来了？这里是你家，但是…
{\fs10}Hey！ What are you doing here？ I mean, it's your house, but…

162
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:49,840
我寄了本我写的书给你，看了吗？
{\fs10}I sent you a copy of my book. Did you get a chance？

163
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:52,950
不，我还没有读
{\fs10}- No, I haven't read it yet. - Mm.

164
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:56,020
我认识你，你是白宫的管理人
{\fs10}I know you. You're the White House curator.

165
00:12:56,090 --> 00:13:00,660
- 我是莱利，我们以前见过面，就在… - 对，你是本的助手
{\fs10}- I'm Riley. We met, uh, back in… - Right. You're, uh, Ben's assistant.

166
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:02,400
什么？
{\fs10}What？

167
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:05,060
也许我该走了
{\fs10}Um, maybe I should go.

168
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:08,770
- 嗯，我真的很… - 明晚一起吃饭好吗？
{\fs10}- Yeah, I'm really… - Dinner tomorrow night？

169
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,070
我明天已经有安排了
{\fs10}I… I actually already have plans for tomorrow.

170
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:13,410
你有吗？
{\fs10}You do？

171
00:13:14,610 --> 00:13:17,340
- 你当然早安排了 - 但我星期五有空
{\fs10}- Of course you do. - But I'm free on Friday.

172
00:13:17,420 --> 00:13:20,510
那太好了
{\fs10}- Awkward. - Oh, great.

173
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:23,710
- 晚安 - 晚安
{\fs10}- Good night. - Good night.

174
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:26,990
真不敢相信，你竟然擅闯民宅
{\fs10}I cannot believe you broke in.

175
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:29,650
- 你拿了什么？ - 都是我自己的东西
{\fs10}- What did you take？ - It's just my things.

176
00:13:31,230 --> 00:13:32,420
交出来，本
{\fs10}Hand it over, Ben.

177
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:35,060
我得去看布斯日记新发现的那页
{\fs10}I need to see the Booth diary page.

178
00:13:35,130 --> 00:13:38,930
你早已经看过了，上面没有藏宝图
{\fs10}You saw the page yourself. There is no treasure map on it.

179
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:42,800
但那上面有发现藏宝图的密码 有人用光谱分析过那页纸吗？
{\fs10}No, it's a cipher leading to a map. Anyone spectral-image the page？

180
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:46,170
没必要，墨水书写的字迹清晰可见
{\fs10}No need to. The ink writing on the page is clearly visible.

181
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,440
可能有的字迹被抹去或者褪色了呢？
{\fs10}It could have been erased or faded.

182
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:51,970
你是文件保管部门的主管，你应该知道
{\fs10}You're the director of document conservation. You know this.

183
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:54,040
不归我管，那不是我的部门
{\fs10}Not up to me. It's not my department.

184
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,640
你管的就是那个部门的上级部门
{\fs10}That department reports to your department.

185
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:59,020
拜托，就用红外线看一次
{\fs10}Come on. One look under infrared.

186
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:01,050
波士顿茶几可以归你
{\fs10}You can have the Boston Tea Tables.

187
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,190
两张都归我？
{\fs10}Both of them？

188
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:14,300
这张纸我们已经看了几个小时了
{\fs10}We've been looking at this page for hours.

189
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:15,960
上面什么都没有
{\fs10}There's nothing there.

190
00:14:16,810 --> 00:14:21,240
本，我认为在这张纸上什么也找不到
{\fs10}Ben, I really don't think we're going to find anything on this page.

191
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:23,750
你不妨这么想，等到一百年之后
{\fs10}In a hundred years, no one's going to remember

192
00:14:23,810 --> 00:14:27,110
提起暗杀林肯的刺客 大家只会记得布斯一个人的名字
{\fs10}anyone involved in the Lincoln assassination besides Booth.

193
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:31,350
这可不一定 记得有句老话叫“他，玛德”么？
{\fs10}That's not true. Do you know the expression, "His name is mud"？

194
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:33,450
- 是的，当然记得 - 你记得？
{\fs10}- Yes. Of course. - You do？

195
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:38,460
- 那你知道这句话的出处吗？ - 除了你还有谁会知道
{\fs10}- You know the origin of the expression？ - Does anyone but you？

196
00:14:38,530 --> 00:14:42,190
塞缪尔・玛德医生被控是刺杀林肯的同谋
{\fs10}Dr. Samuel Mudd was convicted of being a co-conspirator

197
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:45,930
后因证据不足，终被法庭释放
{\fs10}in the Lincoln assassination. The evidence was circumstantial.

198
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,800
但那已经无济于事了
{\fs10}He was later pardoned, but it didn't matter.

199
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:53,640
到现在玛德这名字都没翻身 我不能让盖茨这两个字蒙羞
{\fs10}Mudd's name still lives in infamy. And I will not let Thomas Gates' name be mud.

200
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:57,780
- 本 - 什么？
{\fs10}- Ben. - What？

201
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,250
看这里
{\fs10}Look at this.

202
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,010
看见没有？
{\fs10}- See that？ - Oh.

203
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:07,850
- 看着好像有字，不是吗？ - 是啊，那几个字好像是“看不清”
{\fs10}- That's quite something, isn't it？ - Yeah. It says "smudge. "

204
00:15:08,730 --> 00:15:10,060
什么都不是啊
{\fs10}It's nothing.

205
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:15,800
是上一页墨水渗透的痕迹，翻过来看看
{\fs10}Residual ink from the facing page. Flip it.

206
00:15:16,470 --> 00:15:18,300
字母是反的
{\fs10}The letters are backwards.

207
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:20,360
- 这是密码 - 没错
{\fs10}- It's a cipher. - Yes. It is.

208
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,740
一组密码，字母是成对的，看见没？
{\fs10}A cipher. See how the letters are coupled？

209
00:15:22,810 --> 00:15:28,580
普莱费厄密码字母就是成对的 这可以证明他所说的不是谎言
{\fs10}Playfair ciphers encode letters in pairs. This could prove his story.

210
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:33,050
除非你能破译密码，但这不能证明什么
{\fs10}Unless you decode the cipher, this does not prove a theory.

211
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,350
那没问题，我们只要找到 由五个字母组成的关键字就行了
{\fs10}That's OK. We need a five-letter keyword.

212
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:37,720
- 那关键字是？ - 我还不知道
{\fs10}- What's the keyword？ - I don't know yet.

213
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:40,550
- 好吧 - 能打印出来给我吗？
{\fs10}- All right. - Uh, can I get a printout of this？

214
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:43,530
英语单词可是成千上万啊
{\fs10}There's a billion words in the English language.

215
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:46,650
还得符合逻辑…让我们从头开始吧
{\fs10}Got to be a logical… Let's start from the beginning.

216
00:15:46,730 --> 00:15:48,290
从A开始…Aardvark{\fs12}（意为土豚）…
{\fs10}A. Aardvark.

217
00:15:48,370 --> 00:15:52,360
我不是故意和你们唱反调 但是我认为已经来不及了
{\fs10}Don't want to rain on your parade here, but I don't think this is gonna stop

218
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:56,400
尼克尔斯博士明天就要 对外宣布有关该页的发现了
{\fs10}Dr. Nichols from announcing the discovery of the page tomorrow.

219
00:15:56,470 --> 00:16:01,280
等一下，能不能请他等我证明了 托马斯的清白之后再宣布呢？
{\fs10}No, now, wait. Can't you ask him to wait until I prove Thomas is innocent？

220
00:16:02,650 --> 00:16:04,310
那假如他不是清白的呢？
{\fs10}What if he isn't innocent？

221
00:16:11,710 --> 00:16:14,110
联邦调查局总部 约翰・埃德加・胡佛大厦

222
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:18,650
长官，我们的老朋友本・盖茨又上新闻了
{\fs10}Sir？ Looks like our old friend Ben Gates is in the news again.

223
00:16:18,730 --> 00:16:20,860
他又发现什么了？亚特兰蒂斯吗？
{\fs10}What did he find now？ Atlantis？

224
00:16:20,930 --> 00:16:23,630
布斯日记的遗失页重现江湖
{\fs10}A guy came forward with a missing Booth diary page.

225
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,760
这还不是最精彩的，听听这个
{\fs10}That's not the best part. Listen to this.

226
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,930
在这张写有暗杀林肯的同谋者名单中
{\fs10}"On the page are the names of the conspirators

227
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:32,030
赫然列有一名之前不为人知的共谋者 托马斯・盖茨
{\fs10}in the Lincoln assassination, as well as a previously unknown conspirator,

228
00:16:32,110 --> 00:16:38,410
托马斯・盖茨据说是寻宝猎人 本杰明・富兰克林・盖茨的曾曾祖父
{\fs10}Thomas Gates. Thomas Gates is said to be the great-great-grandfather of treasure hunter Benjamin Franklin Gates. "

229
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:42,380
- 我还以为就我的亲戚是坏蛋呢 - 这个威尔金森是什么来头？
{\fs10}- Thought my relatives were bad. - What do we know about this Wilkinson？

230
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:46,650
- 长官？ - 就是这个拿出这张纸的家伙
{\fs10}- Sir？ - Guy claims he had this page

231
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:50,060
都藏了140年，为什么今天才跳出来？
{\fs10}for 140 years then just suddenly comes forward with it？

232
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:54,400
- 为什么？ - 我们会查清楚的
{\fs10}- Why？ - We'll find out.

233
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:55,760
不错
{\fs10}Better.

234
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:57,930
Bacon{\fs12}（培根）
{\fs10}Bacon.

235
00:17:01,110 --> 00:17:02,800
- 继续 - 这样太傻了
{\fs10}- Keep going. - That's stupid.

236
00:17:08,050 --> 00:17:11,070
- 你老爹怎样了？ - 接着干你的
{\fs10}- How's he doing？ - Keep working.

237
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:15,680
我们非常感激威尔金森家族
{\fs10}We're grateful to the Wilkinson family

238
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,450
能将这张纸公诸于世
{\fs10}for coming forth with the page.

239
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:22,390
该页日记上列有之前不为人知的共谋者 托马斯・盖茨
{\fs10}On the page is a name of a previously unknown conspirator, Thomas Gates.

240
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:25,990
- 尼克尔斯也中邪了，看过这个没有？ - 爸爸，别看那个了
{\fs10}- Nichols has bought into it. See？ - Would you stop watching that.

241
00:17:28,170 --> 00:17:29,500
都已经传上网了
{\fs10}It's on the Internet！

242
00:17:30,330 --> 00:17:33,770
- 势不可挡了 - 盖茨可能就是策划者…
{\fs10}- No stopping it now. - Gates may have been the architect…

243
00:17:34,710 --> 00:17:38,440
- 没有一点同情心 - 你知道真相，这就足够了
{\fs10}- They have no understanding. - You know the truth.That's all that matters.

244
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:40,810
你从查尔斯爷爷那里听到的故事才是真的
{\fs10} You heard the story from Grandpa.

245
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:45,250
故事？那家伙拿出的是证据 他就能证明一切
{\fs10}The story？ This guy's got evidence. He's got everything.

246
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:47,150
我们只有故事，什么都没法证明
{\fs10}We have a story. We have nothing.

247
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:50,750
盖茨家族扬眉吐气才没多久
{\fs10}For one brief moment, the Gates family could hold its head up.

248
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:53,880
- 现在又变成一群疯子了 - 但我们不是骗子
{\fs10}- Now we're a bunch of crazies. - But we're not liars.

249
00:17:55,090 --> 00:18:01,860
威尔金森说是托马斯・盖茨一手策划了 美国历史上最黑暗的时刻
{\fs10}Wilkinson is saying that Thomas Gates was a mastermind to one of the darkest hours in U.S. History.

250
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:04,490
而且为了掩盖真相，他还焚烧了日记
{\fs10}And he burned the diary page to cover that up.

251
00:18:05,270 --> 00:18:07,670
但你我都知道他之所以烧掉那页日记
{\fs10}You and I both know he burned the page

252
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:10,230
是为了阻止布斯和他的人找到宝藏
{\fs10}to keep Booth's men from finding the treasure.

253
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:12,100
那就是我们要去证明的东西
{\fs10}That's what we're going to prove.

254
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:14,670
- 只有一个方法能证明 - 得找到宝藏
{\fs10}- Only one way to prove it. - Find the treasure.

255
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:18,110
必须找到它，而且你得帮我一起找
{\fs10}You've got to find it. You're going to help me find it. So come on.

256
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,880
把查尔斯爷爷说过的故事再讲一遍
{\fs10}Let's hear the story again from Grandpa Charles.

257
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:25,510
爷爷听到他爸爸说到“藏宝图”
{\fs10}Grandpa heard his father say, "Treasure map. "

258
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:29,650
- 然后外面就乱起来了 - 那些都说过了，之后呢？
{\fs10}- Then there was a commotion. - Got all that. Anything after that？

259
00:18:29,730 --> 00:18:33,290
他有说过什么，做过什么吗？随便什么
{\fs10}Anything he said, something he did？ Anything at all？

260
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:36,190
- 慢着… - 怎么了？
{\fs10}- Wait a minute. - What？

261
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:41,460
他握住他儿子的手
{\fs10}He took his son's hand.

262
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:45,630
看着儿子的眼睛，用最后一口气说到
{\fs10}He looked him in the eye, and he said, with his dying breath,

263
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:50,580
- 凡人皆要还之债 - 凡人皆要还之债？
{\fs10}- "The debt that all men pay. " - "The debt that all men pay"？

264
00:18:50,650 --> 00:18:52,780
托马斯已经还了
{\fs10}The debt that Thomas paid.

265
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:55,180
是五个字母
{\fs10}That's five letters.

266
00:18:56,890 --> 00:18:58,010
试试“Death”{\fs12}（死亡）
{\fs10}Try "Death. "

267
00:18:58,060 --> 00:18:59,820
- 什么？ - 是密钥
{\fs10}- What？ - It's the keycode.

268
00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:01,720
凡人皆要还之债，就是死亡
{\fs10}The debt that all men pay is death.

269
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:07,520
好的
{\fs10}All right.

270
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:12,430
L，A，B，O，U，L
{\fs10}L-A-B-O-U-L…

271
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:15,070
是Lab…ool…
{\fs10}It's Lab-ool…

272
00:19:15,140 --> 00:19:19,340
Lab…ahl…La…
{\fs10}Lab-ahl… La…

273
00:19:19,410 --> 00:19:20,570
哪儿来这么个词啊
{\fs10}It's gibberish.

274
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,870
- Laboulaye - 拉布莱伊
{\fs10}- Laboulaye！ - Laboulaye！

275
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:25,570
- 是什么？ - 是人名，爱德华・拉布莱伊
{\fs10}- What is that？ - It's a who. Edward Laboulaye.

276
00:19:25,650 --> 00:19:26,670
电话在哪？
{\fs10}Where's the phone？

277
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:29,450
我不知道，这里乱的一塌糊涂
{\fs10}I don't know. Can't find anything in this mess.

278
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:33,510
- 只是暂时的，找到新地方我就搬走 - 还是找老地方吧，我喜欢她
{\fs10}- Temporary till I find a new place. - Find the old one. I like her.

279
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:37,790
- 嗨 - 蔡斯博士
{\fs10}- Hi. - Dr. Chase.

280
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:40,020
- 请叫我阿比盖尔 - 阿比盖尔
{\fs10}- Abigail, please. - Abigail.

281
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,400
- 幸会 - 请坐
{\fs10}- Nice to meet you. - Have a seat.

282
00:19:45,870 --> 00:19:48,030
感谢你能来与我相见
{\fs10}Thanks for agreeing to meet with me.

283
00:19:48,110 --> 00:19:51,910
别客气，关于那日记，我正想打电话给你
{\fs10}Of course. I was actually going to call you about the diary page.

284
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:54,210
- 有新的消息？ - 嗯…
{\fs10}- Any news？ - Well…

285
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:58,610
在上面发现了一些肉眼难辨的字母组合
{\fs10}We actually found some latent letter fragments on it.

286
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,240
你看
{\fs10}Take a look.

287
00:20:03,450 --> 00:20:05,820
无意义的字母，是密码？
{\fs10}Random letters. A cipher？

288
00:20:05,890 --> 00:20:07,520
- 也许 - 盖茨看过了吗？
{\fs10}- Maybe. - Gates seen this？

289
00:20:07,590 --> 00:20:09,650
就是他发现的
{\fs10}He's the one that discovered it.

290
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:13,260
- 抱歉 - 没关系
{\fs10}- I'm sorry. - Not a problem.

291
00:20:15,730 --> 00:20:18,360
- 请等我一分钟 - 请便
{\fs10}- I need one minute. - Please, take your time.

292
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:19,630
嘿，怎么了？
{\fs10}Hey. What？

293
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:22,170
我们破译了密码，明文是“拉布莱伊”
{\fs10}We cracked the cipher. It's "Laboulaye. "

294
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,970
密码的结果是“拉布莱伊”
{\fs10}The cipher spells "Laboulaye. "

295
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:28,070
拉布莱伊在法国是名人，这可能并不代表什么
{\fs10}So？ Laboulaye was well-known in France. It could be nothing.

296
00:20:28,150 --> 00:20:31,840
也许如托马斯・盖茨所说，确实有张藏宝图
{\fs10}Or maybe there was a treasure map like Thomas Gates said there was,

297
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:35,150
而且藏宝图说不定就在拉布莱伊手上 后面还有一个单词，只有开头的部分
{\fs10}and Laboulaye had it. We only got a partial on the next word.

298
00:20:35,220 --> 00:20:37,380
L，A，D，lad…ladder…
{\fs10}L- A-D, lad… ladder…

299
00:20:37,450 --> 00:20:39,120
- L，A，D… - 阿拉丁，阿拉丁？
{\fs10}- L-A-D. - Aladdin！ Aladdin？

300
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:41,590
- Lady - 谢谢你，阿比盖尔
{\fs10}- Lady！ - Thank you, Abigail！

301
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:45,690
“拉布莱伊的女士” 你知道拉布莱伊曾策划过什么吗？
{\fs10}Laboulaye Lady. Do you know what Laboulaye was planning

302
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:48,390
就在林肯被暗杀期间
{\fs10}right around the time Lincoln was assassinated？

303
00:20:48,470 --> 00:20:50,590
好了，本，我要挂了
{\fs10}OK, Ben, I've got to go.

304
00:20:50,670 --> 00:20:53,140
藏宝图或藏宝图的线索就在神像上…
{\fs10}There's a map or a clue to a map on the Statue…

305
00:20:53,970 --> 00:20:56,630
- 她挂了 - 她肯接你的电话，已经不错了
{\fs10}- She hung up. - She took your call. That was good.

306
00:20:56,740 --> 00:20:59,400
- 盖茨博士 - 嗯
{\fs10}- Dr. Gates？ - Yes.

307
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:04,650
刚才我禁不住偷听了几句，他破译了密码？
{\fs10}Sounds like he cracked the cipher. I couldn't help but overhear.

308
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,780
拉布莱伊，是说爱德华・拉布莱伊？
{\fs10}Laboulaye？ As in Edouard Laboulaye？

309
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:10,450
他似乎是那么讲的
{\fs10}He seems to believe so, yes.

310
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,920
自由女神像就是根据他的想法建造的
{\fs10}Man who had the idea for the Statue of Liberty.

311
00:21:12,990 --> 00:21:16,220
你说藏宝图在自由女神像上？
{\fs10}You're saying there's a treasure map in the Statue of Liberty？

312
00:21:16,290 --> 00:21:20,200
拉布莱伊曾是个石匠，石匠喜欢 在自己的建筑作品中留下些线索
{\fs10}Laboulaye was a Mason. They built clues into everything.

313
00:21:20,260 --> 00:21:22,130
是从我的书里读到的吧
{\fs10}Did you learn that from my book？

314
00:21:25,170 --> 00:21:27,800
- 对历史有兴趣吗？ - 为之着迷
{\fs10}- Have an interest in history？ - Fascinated by it.

315
00:21:28,410 --> 00:21:31,340
尤其是南北战争
{\fs10}Civil War, especially. My family's descended from

316
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:34,710
我家是南部邦联将军阿尔伯特・派克的后裔 他是个了不起的人物
{\fs10}Confederate General Albert Pike. He was a remarkable man.

317
00:21:34,780 --> 00:21:38,980
历史不就是一尊伟人功绩的纪念碑吗？
{\fs10}But, then again, what is history but a marker for the deeds of great men？

318
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:44,210
凡人只有一世，但历史会永远铭记你
{\fs10}A man only has one lifetime, but history can remember you forever.

319
00:21:44,290 --> 00:21:47,450
现在问题在于，是哪一座自由女神像？
{\fs10}So the only question is, which Statue of Liberty？

320
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:48,620
没错
{\fs10}Exactly.

321
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:50,990
还有第二座？
{\fs10}Is there more than one？

322
00:21:52,130 --> 00:21:54,620
实际上有三座，莱利
{\fs10}There are three, actually, Riley.

323
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:59,140
一座在纽约，一座在卢森堡公园
{\fs10}One is in New York, one in the Luxembourg Garden.

324
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:02,040
但他只把其中的一座称为“女士”
{\fs10}But he only referred to one as his "lady. "

325
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:04,640
法国  巴黎

326
00:22:18,820 --> 00:22:21,590
你的做法太不可思议了
{\fs10}This is like, impossible, what you're doing.

327
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:23,290
你的欣赏是我的荣幸
{\fs10}I'm glad you're enjoying it.

328
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:27,390
拉布莱伊一定在那上面留下了线索 去看看火炬
{\fs10}Laboulaye had to leave a clue somewhere on here. Move in on the torch.

329
00:22:27,460 --> 00:22:30,300
让我来，这可不象看起来那么容易
{\fs10}Let me get there. It's not as easy as it looks.

330
00:22:30,370 --> 00:22:32,770
我知道，我明白
{\fs10}No. Believe me, I understand.

331
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,530
抱歉，警官，什么事？
{\fs10}Excuse me, officer. May I help you？

332
00:22:39,010 --> 00:22:41,880
美国人吧？
{\fs10}Ah, American, eh？

333
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:46,810
在你们看来也许没什么大不了的 但你们扰乱了其他人宁静的早晨
{\fs10}Of course you see no problem in disturbing everyone's pleasant morning

334
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:49,250
- 就是那个嗡嗡的东西 - 嘿
{\fs10}- with your buzzing there. - Hey！

335
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:53,620
多亏了你们法国人，才有我们国家的宪法 就是那个孟德斯鸠
{\fs10}You know how much our constitution was influenced by your man, Montesquieu？

336
00:22:53,690 --> 00:22:55,420
- 你知道孟德斯鸠？ - 找到了
{\fs10}- You know Montesquieu？ - Got it.

337
00:22:57,790 --> 00:23:01,030
孟德斯鸠，当然知道啦 “我们要建立一个政府…”
{\fs10}Montesquieu, yeah. "A government should be set up so that… "

338
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:04,190
“使人不必再惧怕他人”
{\fs10}"… no man need be afraid of another. "

339
00:23:04,770 --> 00:23:06,500
- 说的好 - 谢谢
{\fs10}- That's very good. - Thank you.

340
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:10,330
- 我很吃惊呀 - 我找到了，找到了
{\fs10}- I'm astonished. - I got it, I got it.

341
00:23:10,670 --> 00:23:13,470
- 希望你看得懂法语 - 我能帮忙吗？
{\fs10}- I hope you read French. - May I？

342
00:23:15,350 --> 00:23:16,780
他可是警察啊
{\fs10}He's a cop.

343
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:22,620
“那双子远渡重洋，坚决…”
{\fs10}Um… "Across the sea these twins stand determined… "

344
00:23:22,690 --> 00:23:25,150
- 坚定 - 坚定，对
{\fs10}- Resolute. - "Resolute," yeah.

345
00:23:25,220 --> 00:23:28,120
“坚定屹立，守护我们的理想”
{\fs10}"… to preserve what we are looking for.

346
00:23:28,190 --> 00:23:32,090
拉布莱伊，1876年
{\fs10}- Uh… Laboulaye, 1876." - Six.

347
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,690
- 这是线索 - 那双子坚定屹立着
{\fs10}- It's a clue. - "These twins stand resolute. "

348
00:23:36,030 --> 00:23:38,700
我想想，坚定的双子
{\fs10}Let's see. Resolute twins.

349
00:23:40,300 --> 00:23:41,700
坚定的
{\fs10}Resolute.

350
00:23:42,470 --> 00:23:45,310
坚定的，而且是双子
{\fs10}Resolute. And then twins.

351
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:51,010
连体婴儿{\fs12}（连体和暹罗同字）？暹罗？ 是说法国与泰国间的航路吗？
{\fs10}Siamese twins？ Siam？ Trade routes between France and Thailand？

352
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:54,650
那绝对不可能… 英国皇家海军舰艇，坚定号
{\fs10}That's ridiculous. HMS Resolute.

353
00:23:55,590 --> 00:24:00,050
19世纪时，这艘船曾在北冰洋失踪
{\fs10}A British ship that got lost in the Arctic in the 1800s.

354
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:05,090
后来这船被美国捕鲸船队发现 美国国会决定将其送还给英国
{\fs10}It was salvaged by American whalers, and then Congress sent it back to England.

355
00:24:05,130 --> 00:24:07,620
这艘军舰退役之后
{\fs10}When the ship was finally retired,

356
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:12,660
维多利亚女王用船上的木料打造了两张书桌
{\fs10}Queen Victoria had two desks made from its timbers.

357
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:15,140
哇塞，坚定的双子
{\fs10}Voil？ Resolute twins.

358
00:24:15,210 --> 00:24:19,540
- 那现在这两张桌子在哪儿？ - 较近的一张在伦敦
{\fs10}- And where are those desks now？ - The closest one is in London.

359
00:24:19,610 --> 00:24:21,910
莱利，我们如何才能尽快到达白金汉宫？
{\fs10}How fast can we get to Buckingham Palace？

360
00:24:21,980 --> 00:24:24,540
不知道，为什么不问问你的新朋友
{\fs10}Don't know. Why don't you ask your new best friend？

361
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:28,640
他会帮你叫出租车
{\fs10}He's going to call you a cab.

362
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,240
好吗？
{\fs10}OK？

363
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:33,980
- 这直升机很棒，是你的吗？ - 对，是我的
{\fs10}- Nice helicopter. Is that yours？ - Yes, actually. It is.

364
00:24:34,060 --> 00:24:38,150
- 好吧，那罚单也是你的 - 太好了
{\fs10}- OK, so you get the ticket. - Great.

365
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:42,220
米奇・威尔金森在弗吉尼亚军事学院主修历史
{\fs10}Mitch Wilkinson studied history at Virginia Military Institute.

366
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:46,170
1978年毕业后他开了一家私人保安公司 海湾战争时公司在伊拉克执行过保安任务
{\fs10}Graduated 1978. Ran a private security company which had contracts in Iraq

367
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:49,030
90年代后期还曾在刚果接了一笔单子
{\fs10}during the invasion, and in the Congo in the late '90s.

368
00:24:49,110 --> 00:24:53,370
他不仅是一名资深雇佣兵 同时还是一个黑市古董商
{\fs10}These are trained mercenaries as well as being black-market antiquities dealers.

369
00:24:54,240 --> 00:25:01,310
一个黑市古董商为什么会 捐献弥足珍贵的南北战争文物呢？
{\fs10}So why does a black market antiquities dealer give up a rare Civil War artifact？

370
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:05,620
完全可以卖给私人收藏家大赚一笔
{\fs10}Something he could sell to a private collector for a good deal of money？

371
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,190
设备1克隆设备2

372
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:48,190
正在传输…正在接收

373
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,690
设备克隆已完成

374
00:26:04,420 --> 00:26:06,020
英国  伦敦

375
00:26:09,050 --> 00:26:11,020
女王办公室在这里
{\fs10}So the queen's office is here.

376
00:26:11,090 --> 00:26:13,180
升降机能带你上去
{\fs10}The elevator shaft gets you close,

377
00:26:13,260 --> 00:26:17,090
但是唯一的通道要经过保安室
{\fs10}but the only direct access is through security.

378
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:20,620
- 真够刺激的 - 得想法子让你先进那房间
{\fs10}- That should be exciting. - We got to get you in that room.

379
00:26:22,270 --> 00:26:23,700
- 嗨，爸爸 - 本
{\fs10}- Hi, Dad. - Ben.

380
00:26:23,770 --> 00:26:26,330
是帕特里克・盖茨打给本的电话
{\fs10}It's Patrick Gates' phone. He's calling Ben.

381
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,460
给我吧
{\fs10}Give me that.

382
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:31,210
昨晚有人闯进我们家，我被袭击了
{\fs10}The house was broken into last night. I was attacked.

383
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:32,800
快报警，我这就回来
{\fs10}Call the police. I'm coming home.

384
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,710
- 怎么了？发生什么事了？ - 那于事无补啊
{\fs10}- What？ - What good would that do？

385
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:37,870
他们什么都没拿，我也没事
{\fs10}They didn't take anything. And besides, I'm fine.

386
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:41,410
好吧，我们在伦敦，正准备去白金汉宫
{\fs10}OK. We're in London. We're going to Buckingham Palace.

387
00:26:41,490 --> 00:26:44,650
明天下午我们和管理人还有约会
{\fs10}We have an appointment with the curator tomorrow afternoon.

388
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,950
- 好的，儿子，小心点，再见 - 再见
{\fs10}- Son, just be careful. Goodbye. - Bye.

389
00:26:47,020 --> 00:26:48,890
还有其他人在打宝藏的主意
{\fs10}Someone else is after the treasure.

390
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:51,360
那是肯定的
{\fs10}Of course someone else is after the treasure.

391
00:26:51,430 --> 00:26:55,300
- 这是寻宝行业的金科玉律 - 我们必须赶快去看那桌子
{\fs10}- It's the axiom of treasure hunting. - We have to hurry and see that desk.

392
00:26:55,370 --> 00:26:57,560
我们可不能错过那个约会哦
{\fs10}We don't want to miss that appointment.

393
00:26:59,740 --> 00:27:02,830
- 嗨，我是本・盖茨 - 西翼安全公司的吧，请进
{\fs10}- Hi. Ben Gates. - See security. They'll let you in.

394
00:27:43,150 --> 00:27:45,810
好，午茶时间到了，伙计们
{\fs10}OK. It's teatime, chaps.

395
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:02,890
我在找管理人办公室，应该怎么走？
{\fs10}Looking for the curator's office. Which way was it again？

396
00:28:02,970 --> 00:28:05,430
顺着楼梯上去，第一条过道左转
{\fs10}Follow the stairs round, then turn first left.

397
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:07,130
非常感谢
{\fs10}Thank you so much.

398
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:14,310
- 本 - 阿比盖尔
{\fs10}- Ben. - Abigail.

399
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:16,610
- 她怎么在这儿？ - 你怎么在这儿？
{\fs10}- What's she doing here？ - What're you doing？

400
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:19,770
你爸爸打电话跟我说的 你的下一条线索在这里
{\fs10}Your dad called me. Said your next clue was here.

401
00:28:19,850 --> 00:28:21,780
- 真的是她？ - 本…
{\fs10}- She's really there？ - Ben…

402
00:28:21,850 --> 00:28:23,320
- 甩掉她，摆脱她 - 我想来帮忙
{\fs10}- Drop her. Lose her. - I want to help.

403
00:28:23,390 --> 00:28:26,150
太好了，但现在不是时候
{\fs10}That's very nice, but it's a bad time right now.

404
00:28:26,220 --> 00:28:29,920
- 现在不是时候？ - 对，不是时候
{\fs10}- A bad time, right now？ - It's a bad time.

405
00:28:29,990 --> 00:28:34,620
那好，我大老远的飞到伦敦来帮你
{\fs10}OK, I just flew all the way to London to offer my help…

406
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:37,100
- 别忘了计划 - 你却不需要？
{\fs10}- Remember the plan. - You don't need it？

407
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,930
你是想来吵架的？
{\fs10}You're the one making a scene.

408
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:42,440
- 我现在没想跟你吵 - 我们倒是需要吵一吵
{\fs10}- I… I'm not making a scene right now. - We want to make a scene.

409
00:28:42,510 --> 00:28:46,130
那好吧，如果你想吵，那就吵
{\fs10}Well then, fine！ If that's what you want, let's have it out now！

410
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:50,410
- 太狡猾了 - 我猜猜？是时机不对？
{\fs10}- So subtle. - Let me guess？ It's the wrong time.

411
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:53,350
还是地方不对？反正又是我的错！
{\fs10}It's the wrong place. I'm wrong again！

412
00:28:53,420 --> 00:28:56,350
我俩的事是我的错 托马斯・盖茨也是我的错
{\fs10}Wrong about us, wrong about Thomas Gates,

413
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:59,010
以为你会喜欢安娜女王式的椅子 也是我的错！
{\fs10}wrong that you'd like the Queen Anne chair！

414
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,110
你错就错在自认为我喜欢那椅子
{\fs10}You're wrong to assume I'd like the chair.

415
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:05,060
大家听见没，都来听听 这比导游讲的好听多了
{\fs10}You see？ Everybody, listen to this. This is more interesting than that.

416
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:08,620
她觉得就算我做对了，也是错 有这道理吗？
{\fs10}She thinks that even when I'm right, I'm wrong！ Isn't that right？

417
00:29:08,700 --> 00:29:12,570
阿比盖尔，如果遇到问题时我抢答了
{\fs10}Abigail, just because I answer a question quickly

418
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:14,000
那也算是错吗？
{\fs10}doesn't make it wrong.

419
00:29:14,070 --> 00:29:17,770
需要我们两人一起做决定的时候 即使你一个人做对了，那也是错
{\fs10}Not if the answer's something we need to figure out as a couple.

420
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:19,540
- 两人相处就该这样 - 先生
{\fs10}- That's what couples do！ - Sir.

421
00:29:19,610 --> 00:29:21,600
能请你和这位小姐，去外面解决吗？
{\fs10}You and your missis, take it outside.

422
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:25,740
看看你都干了什么，你把小警察都招来了
{\fs10}Now look what you've done. You've brought the little bobbies down on us！

423
00:29:25,820 --> 00:29:28,780
你把这位小姐带出去吧，我要留在这
{\fs10}You take the missis outside. I'm staying right here.

424
00:29:29,490 --> 00:29:31,390
本
{\fs10}- Ben！ - Whee！

425
00:29:31,450 --> 00:29:33,180
- 下午好，先生 - {\fs12}（学英国口音）你好
{\fs10}- Good afternoon, sir. - Hello.

426
00:29:33,260 --> 00:29:35,720
- 喝酒了，是吧？ - 就一点
{\fs10}- Been drinking, have we？ - Just a nip.

427
00:29:35,790 --> 00:29:38,820
到酒吧喝了那么一品脱而已，没事的
{\fs10}Popped down to the pub for a pint！ Bit of all right！

428
00:29:38,900 --> 00:29:44,370
因为我喜欢威士忌，就要拘捕我？
{\fs10}Going to arrest a man for that？Going to detain a blighter for enjoying his whiskey？

429
00:29:44,430 --> 00:29:46,030
- 够了 - 香肠炖薯泥
{\fs10}- Enough. - Bangers and mash.

430
00:29:46,100 --> 00:29:47,730
土豆炒包菜，烟熏烤鳗派
{\fs10}Bubbles and squeak. Smoked eel pie.

431
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:48,830
- 先生 - 杂碎八宝菜
{\fs10}- Sir！ - Haggis！

432
00:29:48,910 --> 00:29:52,770
- 够了，给我下来 - 我还买了一大堆椰子！
{\fs10}- That's it！ Dismount the banister！ - I've got a lovely bunch of coconuts！

433
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:54,940
它们就在那儿，排排坐呀…
{\fs10}Here they are, standing in a row！

434
00:29:55,010 --> 00:29:58,070
小个的，大个的，有的就像你脑袋那么大
{\fs10}Small ones, big ones, some as big as your head！

435
00:29:58,150 --> 00:30:00,640
太有才了
{\fs10}That was brilliant.

436
00:30:01,250 --> 00:30:05,090
- 作出正确的决定也有错？ - 没错，你也该试着去正确一次
{\fs10}- What's wrong with being right？ - Nothing. You should try it sometime.

437
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:08,220
- 你是说我从来没做对过？ - 我可没那么说
{\fs10}- You're saying that I'm never right？ - I did not say that.

438
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:10,420
那我是不是又错了？
{\fs10}Hoo！ So I'm wrong again.

439
00:30:10,730 --> 00:30:13,590
- 瞧瞧，你总算对一次了 - 好得很啊，妙到巅啊
{\fs10}- Now, see, there you are correct. - Capital. Topper.

440
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:17,900
你妈妈早跟我说过了
{\fs10}Your mother told me about you.

441
00:30:18,870 --> 00:30:23,430
- 进去 - 那你为什么不干脆列个清单呢
{\fs10}- In here, please. - Why don't you just make a list

442
00:30:23,510 --> 00:30:26,670
上面写好我能说什么，不能说什么
{\fs10}of what's OK for me to say or not write something…

443
00:30:27,340 --> 00:30:29,640
- 每次都是你自己独自判断对错 - 你们两只唧喳鸟，待在这儿吧
{\fs10}- What's right or wrong… - You two, stay.

444
00:30:29,710 --> 00:30:31,680
- 好吗？ - 别，不要，伙计
{\fs10}- Right？ - No！ No, no, man.

445
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:35,010
- 别把我关在这儿 - 哇哦
{\fs10}- Don't leave me in here！ - That's great. Wow.

446
00:30:35,620 --> 00:30:37,050
怎么回事情？
{\fs10}What is going on？

447
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:41,060
很抱歉把你也卷进来 但你的表演真得很棒
{\fs10}I'm sorry for getting you roped into this, but you were excellent.

448
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:44,220
- 承蒙夸奖，你也不赖 - 你是什么时候察觉的？
{\fs10}- Thank you. So were you. - When did you figure out

449
00:30:44,290 --> 00:30:47,020
- 察觉我是假装和你吵的？ - 就在我们假吵的时候…
{\fs10}- it was a fake argument？ - When'd you figure out I was

450
00:30:47,100 --> 00:30:49,760
- 你什么时候察觉到我是真在和你吵？ - 就是吵到一半的时候
{\fs10}- arguing during the fake argument？ - The middle.

451
00:30:49,830 --> 00:30:52,770
你说我自以为是的时候… 莱利，快让我们出去
{\fs10}Where "I assume I'm right. " Get us out. Which I don't get.

452
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:55,770
我不明白为什么我自认为是对的 并做对了之后却仍然是错的
{\fs10}If I'm right, after I assume I'm right, then I'm correct.

453
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:58,270
你没有问我就私自决定
{\fs10}When you get to a conclusion without asking,

454
00:30:58,380 --> 00:31:01,370
而你又碰巧做对的话，那不过是你走运而已
{\fs10}and you happen to be right, you got lucky.

455
00:31:02,950 --> 00:31:04,470
那看来我总是走运
{\fs10}I get lucky a lot.

456
00:31:04,950 --> 00:31:07,080
那么，你当我是摆设咯，本？
{\fs10}So where does that leave me, Ben？

457
00:31:07,150 --> 00:31:09,380
你们俩实在是绝配啊
{\fs10}You guys are so great together.

458
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:11,350
- 想知道我为什么要来这儿吗？ - 当然
{\fs10}- Want to know why I'm here？ - Uh-huh.

459
00:31:13,390 --> 00:31:16,790
我认为女王书房的坚定之桌里可能有线索
{\fs10}Think there may be a clue on the Resolute desk in the queen's study.

460
00:31:18,630 --> 00:31:20,030
明白没有？
{\fs10}Does that help？

461
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:24,560
我就不明白为什么对你来说 和别人一起做决定会那么难
{\fs10}Don't understand why it's difficult for you to include others in your decisions.

462
00:31:24,630 --> 00:31:28,160
即使你能猜到我的回答
{\fs10}Just because you may know what my answer is going to be

463
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:30,800
也不代表你就可以不问我啊
{\fs10}doesn't mean you don't have to ask me.

464
00:31:31,370 --> 00:31:34,280
一号门，开启中
{\fs10}Door number one, opening.

465
00:31:36,350 --> 00:31:38,440
好吧，我们来试试看
{\fs10}OK. Let me try this out.

466
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:42,610
阿比盖尔，请你跟我一起去好吗
{\fs10}Abigail, would you like to come with me, please？

467
00:31:42,690 --> 00:31:44,450
好的，谢谢
{\fs10}Yes. Thank you.

468
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:46,150
搞笑，你得留在这儿
{\fs10}Ridiculous. You're staying.

469
00:31:46,220 --> 00:31:48,160
- 太危险了 - 那我也要去
{\fs10}- It's too dangerous. - I am so coming.

470
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:50,780
- 二号门 - 二号门，马上好
{\fs10}- Door number two. - Door two, coming up.

471
00:31:51,930 --> 00:31:53,790
- 你不准去 - 那你叫保安啊
{\fs10}- You're not coming. - Call security.

472
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:57,390
你应该就在升降梯旁边了
{\fs10}You should be near a service elevator.

473
00:31:57,500 --> 00:31:59,700
你干嘛？送花给女王吗？
{\fs10}What are you doing？ Are those for the queen？

474
00:31:59,740 --> 00:32:03,760
女王不在这，王旗没有升起 所以女王应该在温莎堡
{\fs10}Queen's not here. There's no flag flying. Queen's at Windsor.

475
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:06,370
- 你想干嘛？ - 去看看桌子，不带你，再见
{\fs10}- What are you doing？ - See the desk, without you.

476
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,040
- 不 - 别让她去
{\fs10}- No. - Don't let her go.

477
00:32:09,110 --> 00:32:10,550
阿比盖尔…
{\fs10}Abigail…

478
00:32:11,650 --> 00:32:13,640
好吧，进来，快进来
{\fs10}All right. Get in. Get in. Get in！

479
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,580
拿着
{\fs10}Hold this.

480
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:25,060
请把花还给我好吗？
{\fs10}Will you give me the flowers back, please？

481
00:32:25,130 --> 00:32:26,190
嗯
{\fs10}Yeah.

482
00:32:32,270 --> 00:32:35,970
- 怎么了？ - 你擦了我送你的香水
{\fs10}- What？ - Wearing the perfume I bought you.

483
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:37,830
那又如何？
{\fs10}So？

484
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,670
那让我闻到了美女的芬芳
{\fs10}So I think it smells kind of pretty.

485
00:32:41,510 --> 00:32:44,670
- 那是花香，本 - 不，不是
{\fs10}- It's the flowers, Ben. - No, it's not.

486
00:32:47,950 --> 00:32:49,420
我们走
{\fs10}Let's go.

487
00:32:54,390 --> 00:32:56,050
好的，现在左转
{\fs10}OK, now turn left.

488
00:32:56,930 --> 00:32:59,660
- 死路 - 我是说向右，右转
{\fs10}- Dead end. - I mean right. Go right.

489
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:09,070
- 这花…花瓣…花蕊… - 好，很好
{\fs10}- The flowers… petals… stamens. - Good. Good.

490
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:18,410
快走，进去
{\fs10}Go, go.

491
00:33:21,420 --> 00:33:22,780
那就是了
{\fs10}That's it.

492
00:33:24,750 --> 00:33:26,380
坚定之桌
{\fs10}The Resolute desk.

493
00:33:27,490 --> 00:33:28,860
我们要找的是…
{\fs10}We're looking for…

494
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:34,760
镌刻的文字或者图案，或者其它什么的
{\fs10}…writing, patterns in the carvings. Could be anything.

495
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:39,630
看这个
{\fs10}Hey, look at this.

496
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:47,840
- 马尔科姆・吉尔瓦里，1880年 - 等一下
{\fs10}- "Malcolm Gilvary, 1880." - Hold on one second.

497
00:33:48,610 --> 00:33:53,070
找到了，马尔科姆・吉尔瓦里，他不是做家具的
{\fs10}Here we go. Malcolm Gilvary. He didn't make furniture.

498
00:33:53,150 --> 00:33:56,240
他是做中国秘盒的
{\fs10}He made Chinese puzzle boxes.

499
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,680
怎么了？
{\fs10}- Oh… - What？

500
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:11,360
我认为这抽屉的工作原理和 保险箱上的密码筒类似
{\fs10}I think these drawers work like tumblers in a safe.

501
00:34:11,430 --> 00:34:14,960
好吧，4张抽屉就是4位阿拉伯数字组合
{\fs10}OK, four drawers… Four-digit combination？

502
00:34:15,910 --> 00:34:17,000
会是年份吗？
{\fs10}What about a year？

503
00:34:17,070 --> 00:34:21,810
我看看，维多利亚女王，生于1819年
{\fs10}Uh, let me see. Queen Victoria, born 1819.

504
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:23,710
那就是一
{\fs10}So you go one…

505
00:34:26,650 --> 00:34:27,640
八
{\fs10}Eight.

506
00:34:32,690 --> 00:34:33,710
一
{\fs10}One.

507
00:34:37,860 --> 00:34:38,920
九
{\fs10}Nine.

508
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:46,870
- 对不对？ - 巴黎女神像火炬上刻的是1876，试试看
{\fs10}- Any luck？ - OK… 1876 was on the inscription on the statue in Paris. Let's try that.

509
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,390
一
{\fs10}One.

510
00:34:50,740 --> 00:34:51,970
八
{\fs10}Eight.

511
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:56,270
七
{\fs10}Seven.

512
00:35:01,050 --> 00:35:02,380
六
{\fs10}Six.

513
00:35:30,710 --> 00:35:31,910
新问题来了
{\fs10}New rules.

514
00:35:32,780 --> 00:35:36,050
这图案，像是印加或阿兹特克的文字
{\fs10}These markings, like Incan or Aztec.

515
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:38,350
我之前从来没见过类似的符号
{\fs10}I have never seen any symbols like this.

516
00:35:38,420 --> 00:35:43,790
这看起来比南北战争可要古老的多
{\fs10}I mean, this looks centuries older than Civil War.

517
00:35:43,860 --> 00:35:45,260
你觉得这上面是什么意思？
{\fs10}What do you think it means？

518
00:35:45,330 --> 00:35:48,860
我怀疑这东西跟暗杀林肯计划有关
{\fs10}I doubt it has anything to do with the plot to assassinate Lincoln.

519
00:35:52,740 --> 00:35:55,030
警报，警报，本，快离开
{\fs10}Mayday. Mayday. Ben, get out of there.

520
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:04,910
- 那两个被拘者去哪了？ - 好，来点响动如何
{\fs10}- Oi！ Where are my detainees？ - OK, let's make some noise.

521
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:10,920
火警响了
{\fs10}The fire alarm's gone off.

522
00:36:10,990 --> 00:36:13,050
老天保佑女王
{\fs10}Uh-oh. God save the queen.

523
00:36:14,090 --> 00:36:16,020
所有人请撤离
{\fs10}All units, go to action zebra.

524
00:36:16,090 --> 00:36:18,190
- 怎么了？ - 还不清楚
{\fs10}- What's going on？ - Haven't the foggiest.

525
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:24,360
肯定是什么人或者什么东西触发的
{\fs10}Someone or something is causing this.

526
00:36:24,430 --> 00:36:27,700
- 各单位检查各自区域 - 没有道理啊
{\fs10}- Check your primary stations. - This doesn't make any sense.

527
00:36:27,770 --> 00:36:31,040
找出信号源，检查公众四区，八区
{\fs10}Find the source terminal and check public areas four and eight.

528
00:36:46,890 --> 00:36:51,020
女士们，先生这边走 谢谢合作，请继续向前走
{\fs10}This way, ladies and gentlemen. Thank you very much. Keep moving.

529
00:36:51,090 --> 00:36:54,720
一直走到喷泉那边
{\fs10}Keep walking until you're on the other side of the fountain.

530
00:36:54,800 --> 00:37:00,130
- 请原谅，请原谅，让一让 - 找到他们了，他们在正门
{\fs10}- Excuse me, excuse me. Coming through. - I got them. They're at the main gate.

531
00:37:17,950 --> 00:37:21,120
- “火花”，别这样 - 好了，我们走
{\fs10}- Oi！ Sparkle. Come on. - OK. Here we go.

532
00:37:21,190 --> 00:37:22,750
我对狗有些过敏
{\fs10}I'm a little bit allergic.

533
00:37:22,830 --> 00:37:24,990
- 谢谢，好了 - 莱利
{\fs10}- Riley. - Thank you. OK.

534
00:37:25,060 --> 00:37:28,390
- 回头见，谢谢，再见 - 坐下，对不起
{\fs10}- See you later. Thank you. Bye-bye. - Sit！ Sorry！

535
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:32,030
谢谢你们等我，东西能让我看看吗？
{\fs10}Thanks for waiting for me. Can I see the thing？

536
00:37:33,540 --> 00:37:34,940
丹尼尔，等等
{\fs10}Daniel, hold it.

537
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,770
那是什么？
{\fs10}What is that？

538
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:41,540
到白金汉宫就为了这块木头？
{\fs10}Went to Buckingham Palace, all I got was this wood？

539
00:37:41,610 --> 00:37:44,270
看看这些符号，以前从来没见过
{\fs10}Look at the symbols. Never seen anything like this.

540
00:37:44,850 --> 00:37:46,580
这是个不可思议的大发现
{\fs10}It's an incredible discovery.

541
00:37:47,750 --> 00:37:51,650
- 威尔金森 - 拦住他们，快，快
{\fs10}- Wilkinson. - Stop them. Go, go, go！

542
00:37:53,590 --> 00:37:56,220
- 那个打宝藏主意的家伙就是他 - 我来开车
{\fs10}- He's the one after the treasure. - I'll drive.

543
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:00,990
这可是英国
{\fs10}We're in England.

544
00:38:08,040 --> 00:38:09,370
有枪，快趴下
{\fs10}It's a gun！ Get down！

545
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:15,940
- 我们被困住了 - 趴下，把头低下
{\fs10}- We're trapped！ - Hang on！ Keep your heads down.

546
00:38:27,390 --> 00:38:28,480
你是谁？
{\fs10}Hey, who are you？

547
00:38:44,510 --> 00:38:45,600
抱歉
{\fs10}Sorry.

548
00:38:57,090 --> 00:39:00,320
- 本，他们追上来了 - 他们想怎么样啊？
{\fs10}- Ben, they're getting closer. - What is their problem？

549
00:39:06,130 --> 00:39:08,220
- 左转，左转 - 抓紧
{\fs10}- Go left！ Go left！ - Hold on.

550
00:39:15,300 --> 00:39:16,600
转弯，转弯
{\fs10}Turn, turn！

551
00:39:17,610 --> 00:39:18,600
小心
{\fs10}Watch out！

552
00:39:25,210 --> 00:39:26,340
大家没事吧？
{\fs10}Everybody OK？

553
00:39:31,620 --> 00:39:34,680
- 快，快点 - 丹尼，让他们停下
{\fs10}- Come on, come on. - Danny, I want them stopped.

554
00:39:39,300 --> 00:39:40,420
小心
{\fs10}Look out！

555
00:40:14,130 --> 00:40:15,460
快，快，快，快
{\fs10}Go. Go, go, go, go！

556
00:40:18,130 --> 00:40:19,620
看到他往哪跑了吗？
{\fs10}Did you see where he went？

557
00:40:24,140 --> 00:40:27,370
- 什么声音？ - 有人电话响，是他打来的
{\fs10}- What is that？ Someone's phone. - It's him.

558
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:30,670
- 你的号码簿里有他的号码？ - 你闭…
{\fs10}- Have his number in your speed dial？ - Oh, shu…

559
00:40:30,750 --> 00:40:32,940
趁还没人受伤，及早收手吧
{\fs10}This has to end before someone gets hurt.

560
00:40:33,020 --> 00:40:36,040
把你在白金汉宫拿到的东西给我 就不会有人受伤
{\fs10}Give me what you got at Buckingham, it won't be necessary.

561
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:37,420
跟我父亲去说吧
{\fs10}Tell that to my father.

562
00:40:40,190 --> 00:40:43,220
白痴
{\fs10}Moron！

563
00:40:43,290 --> 00:40:45,780
他们干嘛站在路中央
{\fs10}Why are they standing in the middle of the street？

564
00:40:48,100 --> 00:40:51,030
- 这些人要去哪？ - 为什么每个人都在跑？
{\fs10}- Where are these people going？ - Why's everyone running？

565
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:56,770
- 他就在后面，快 - 快开
{\fs10}- He's right there！ Go！ - Move！

566
00:40:59,310 --> 00:41:01,240
让开！
{\fs10}Get out of the way！

567
00:41:03,210 --> 00:41:06,610
- 我好像压到谁的脚了 - 小心人群
{\fs10}- Did I just run over a man's foot？ - Watch the people！

568
00:41:15,260 --> 00:41:16,880
快，快，快点
{\fs10}Go！ Go！ Faster！

569
00:41:29,510 --> 00:41:31,370
- 就在那儿 - 看到他们了
{\fs10}- Right over there. - I got them.

570
00:41:32,710 --> 00:41:35,510
- 他们还跟着我们 - 这手机能拍照吗？
{\fs10}- They're still behind us. - This phone have a camera？

571
00:41:35,580 --> 00:41:39,070
- 不能拍，手机坏了 - 好吧，把木板给我
{\fs10}- No. No, it's broken. - All right. Give me the plank.

572
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:45,280
坐稳，我们要闯红灯了
{\fs10}Hang on. We're going to run a red light.

573
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,960
侵入伦敦警局的数据库 找出交通探头拍的照片
{\fs10}Hack into the London Police database and get a picture from that traffic cam.

574
00:42:00,070 --> 00:42:02,700
- 知道啦老大 - 怎么，你不行吗？
{\fs10}- Okey-dokey. - You can't do it？

575
00:42:02,740 --> 00:42:05,610
我行的，我就是不喜欢你自以为我行
{\fs10}No, I can. I just don't like that you assume that I can.

576
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:08,240
谢谢你，莱利
{\fs10}Why, thank you, Riley.

577
00:42:31,330 --> 00:42:32,460
去拿
{\fs10}Get it！

578
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:36,830
停车，停车
{\fs10}Stop！ Stop！

579
00:42:57,860 --> 00:42:59,730
- 他拿到了 - 是什么东西？
{\fs10}- He's got it. - What is it？

580
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:02,200
不知道，但是归我们了，走
{\fs10}I don't know, but it's ours. Let's go.

581
00:43:06,770 --> 00:43:07,440
华盛顿特区

582
00:43:10,770 --> 00:43:13,440
- 阿比盖尔 - 嘿，帕特里克
{\fs10}- Abigail！ - Hey, Patrick.

583
00:43:14,610 --> 00:43:16,600
真高兴看见你们俩又在一起了
{\fs10}Nice to see you two together again.

584
00:43:16,680 --> 00:43:18,870
- 嗯，其实我们没有 - 嗯
{\fs10}- Yeah, well, we're not. - Yeah.

585
00:43:18,950 --> 00:43:22,410
我还以为能把这些箱子弄出去了呢
{\fs10}Oh, I was hoping to get some of these boxes out of the house.

586
00:43:31,530 --> 00:43:35,590
我看不太懂这玩意
{\fs10}I can't read the whole thing, but I can tell you that

587
00:43:35,660 --> 00:43:39,160
但我告诉你们，这些文字肯定是 在殖民时代之前的美洲土著留下的
{\fs10}these are definitely pre-colonial Native American markings.

588
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:42,640
- 历史远不止500年 - 远远不止
{\fs10}- Easily 500 years old. - Easily.

589
00:43:46,580 --> 00:43:49,410
我认得其中一个符号
{\fs10}I can identify one symbol.

590
00:43:49,950 --> 00:43:52,540
看看这个，你知道那是什么吗？
{\fs10}Look at this. Do you know what that is？

591
00:43:52,620 --> 00:43:54,580
宗教历法？我不知道
{\fs10}Sacred calendrical？ I don't know.

592
00:43:55,050 --> 00:43:57,610
那个符号是“锡沃拉”
{\fs10}That symbol is Cibola.

593
00:43:58,420 --> 00:43:59,550
“锡沃拉”
{\fs10}That's Cibola.

594
00:44:01,060 --> 00:44:02,960
就是黄金之城
{\fs10}The City of Gold.

595
00:44:03,560 --> 00:44:04,820
黄金之城
{\fs10}The City of Gold.

596
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:11,820
1527年，一艘西班牙船在佛罗里达海岸失事
{\fs10}"In 1527, a Spanish ship wrecked on the Florida coast.

597
00:44:11,900 --> 00:44:13,770
只有四人生还
{\fs10}There were only four survivors.

598
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:18,830
其中一个是名叫埃斯特班的奴隶 他救了当地部落酋长一命
{\fs10}One was a slave named Esteban who saved a local tribe's dying chief.

599
00:44:18,910 --> 00:44:21,740
作为回报，他被带到部落的圣城
{\fs10}As a reward, he was taken to their sacred city,

600
00:44:21,810 --> 00:44:23,710
一座由黄金打造的城市
{\fs10}a city built from solid gold.

601
00:44:25,680 --> 00:44:29,740
后来，埃斯特班想重新找到这座城市 但再也没能找到
{\fs10}Later, when Esteban tried to find the city again, he never could.

602
00:44:29,820 --> 00:44:35,450
但这故事却越传越广，每个来到新大陆的 探险家都在寻找这城市
{\fs10}But the legend grew, and every explorer came to the New World in search of it.

603
00:44:36,390 --> 00:44:40,350
1876年，当卡斯特将军一班寻宝人马 在小巨角被土著全歼之后
{\fs10}When General Custer's search for gold ended with his last stand

604
00:44:40,430 --> 00:44:44,870
寻找黄金城的最后一丝希望也破灭了
{\fs10}at Little Bighorn, it became clear none would ever find it. "

605
00:44:50,510 --> 00:44:55,240
本，想想看，如果南方邦联找到黄金城…
{\fs10}Ben, can you imagine if the Confederates got their hands on the City of Gold…

606
00:44:55,980 --> 00:44:57,450
天啊
{\fs10}My God.

607
00:44:58,380 --> 00:44:59,970
我要找她谈谈
{\fs10}I'm going to go talk to her.

608
00:45:03,850 --> 00:45:06,250
- 你也一起去 - 不！
{\fs10}- You're coming with me. - No！

609
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:10,590
- 除了她没有别人能翻译这个 - 有其他人选的
{\fs10}- Hey. No one else can translate it. - There are others.

610
00:45:10,660 --> 00:45:12,020
有好几个其他人选呢
{\fs10}There are several others.

611
00:45:12,090 --> 00:45:14,430
说到古代美洲土著文明，没人比她更合适了
{\fs10}For ancient Native American？ No one better.

612
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:17,490
- 说谁啊？ - 瞧，本，我不能和你一起去
{\fs10}- Who？ - Look, Ben, I can't go with you.

613
00:45:17,570 --> 00:45:20,760
- 已经，已经25年了 - 32年了
{\fs10}- It's been, what？ Twenty-five years. - Thirty-two.

614
00:45:22,440 --> 00:45:23,670
有那么久了？
{\fs10}That long？

615
00:45:24,410 --> 00:45:28,100
之所以我们32年没有说过话是有原因的
{\fs10}There's a reason why we haven't spoken in 32 years.

616
00:45:28,180 --> 00:45:30,870
- 我们根本没有共通之处 - 那我呢？
{\fs10}- We have nothing in common. - Me？

617
00:45:31,550 --> 00:45:35,380
当然啦，我肯定她和我一样，都以你为傲
{\fs10}Yes, of course. And I'm sure she's just as proud of you as I am.

618
00:45:35,450 --> 00:45:37,850
- 谁啊？ - 他妈妈
{\fs10}- Who？ - His mom.

619
00:45:37,850 --> 00:45:39,820
马里兰大学

620
00:45:40,820 --> 00:45:44,950
- 放松点好吗？没事的 - 当然啦，是该往好的方面想
{\fs10}- Will you relax？ It's gonna be fine. - Sure. Should look at the bright side.

621
00:45:45,030 --> 00:45:48,790
过去那么久了，也许她失忆了，不认得我了
{\fs10}Been a long time. Maybe she lost her memory, won't recognize me.

622
00:45:49,630 --> 00:45:51,030
我恨她！
{\fs10}I hate her！

623
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:54,560
没错就是这儿了
{\fs10}We're in the right place.

624
00:45:57,710 --> 00:46:00,870
我可不想趟这汪浑水
{\fs10}I'm gonna take myself out of the line of fire for this one.

625
00:46:00,940 --> 00:46:02,770
- 嗨，妈妈 - 本杰明
{\fs10}- Hi, Mom. - Benjamin！

626
00:46:02,850 --> 00:46:06,010
阿比盖尔，好一个惊喜啊，你好，亲爱的
{\fs10}Abigail！ What a surprise！ Hello, sweetheart.

627
00:46:11,020 --> 00:46:14,510
看见没？就一个叹词，心里藏着刀呢
{\fs10}You see？ One syllable, a knife in the heart.

628
00:46:14,590 --> 00:46:16,460
- 不至于吧 - 她做得出来
{\fs10}- Oh, no. - She can do that.

629
00:46:16,530 --> 00:46:19,390
正好借这机会问问，我那两把牙刷的下落
{\fs10}I can also track the whereabouts of my toothbrush.

630
00:46:19,460 --> 00:46:22,450
不是我把牙刷丢在马拉喀什的
{\fs10}I was not the one that left the toothbrushes in Marrakech.

631
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:25,500
照你说的，我把它们都放到旅行包里了
{\fs10}I stowed them both in the travel case, as instructed.

632
00:46:25,570 --> 00:46:29,700
对，但是你坚持要负责把行李放上车的
{\fs10}Yes, and you also insisted on loading the luggage into the taxi.

633
00:46:29,770 --> 00:46:32,870
- 我没坚持，而且我的确把行李放上车了 - 对，但你没有拿旅行包
{\fs10}- Didn't insist. I loaded the luggage. - Not the travel case.

634
00:46:32,940 --> 00:46:36,140
旅行包不是行李箱好不好 包应该是打在行李箱里的
{\fs10}Travel case is not luggage. The case goes into the luggage.

635
00:46:36,210 --> 00:46:39,580
- 是谁负责打包行李的呢？ - 我没法把旅行包装进行李箱
{\fs10}- Who was in charge of packing？ - I couldn't get the case into

636
00:46:39,650 --> 00:46:42,710
因为里面塞了你买的蠢毯子
{\fs10}the luggage. It was full with that stupid rug you bought.

637
00:46:42,790 --> 00:46:44,880
你以为上面绣有某种秘密
{\fs10}You thought it had secret stitching.

638
00:46:44,950 --> 00:46:47,390
- 你说那有多蠢？ - 那上面的确绣有秘密
{\fs10}- How stupid was that？ - Did have stitching.

639
00:46:47,460 --> 00:46:50,820
- 六只绿色假皮皮箱… - 妈妈
{\fs10}- Six phony green leather suitcases… - Mom.

640
00:46:53,130 --> 00:46:55,120
我需要你帮忙看下这个
{\fs10}I need you to take a look at this.

641
00:46:56,300 --> 00:46:58,820
- 这是什么照片？ - 这东西很有意思
{\fs10}- What is that a picture of？ - It's interesting.

642
00:46:58,930 --> 00:47:02,030
- 我们认为可能是奥尔麦克文字{\fs12}（奥尔麦克：墨西哥东南的神秘古印第安种族）{\fs18} - 是的
{\fs10}- We think it might be Olmec. - It is.

643
00:47:02,710 --> 00:47:05,230
是索克语没错，不过更古老
{\fs10}Yes, yes, definitely proto-Zoquean.

644
00:47:05,310 --> 00:47:08,470
我们希望你能翻译一下
{\fs10}We were hoping that you could translate it.

645
00:47:09,210 --> 00:47:10,800
嗯，你们肯定是为了这个才来的
{\fs10}Yes, of course you were.

646
00:47:13,650 --> 00:47:16,980
这不会又跟寻宝有关吧，是不是？
{\fs10}Oh, this doesn't involve another treasure hunt, does it？

647
00:47:17,050 --> 00:47:19,850
妈妈，这个确实非常重要
{\fs10}Mom, this is actually very important.

648
00:47:21,820 --> 00:47:24,260
好吧，看看有些什么
{\fs10}All right. What have we got here？

649
00:47:24,990 --> 00:47:29,690
这个…这个象形字…意思是“鸟” 那个么…
{\fs10}This… this glyph here, that means "bird. " And that means…

650
00:47:35,640 --> 00:47:36,760
恩，是尊鸟
{\fs10}Uh, "noble bird. "

651
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:43,370
尊鸟有缘，伸手相牵 圣殿已近，路在眼前
{\fs10}"Find the noble bird, let him take you by the hand and give you passage to the sacred temple. "

652
00:47:50,090 --> 00:47:53,250
你们认为这是黄金城的藏宝图，是吧？
{\fs10}Oh, you think this is a treasure map for Cibola, don't you？

653
00:47:53,790 --> 00:47:55,650
嗯，正是如此
{\fs10}Well, that is exactly what it is.

654
00:47:55,720 --> 00:47:59,850
不，那个符号不是指黄金城 而是指世界的中心
{\fs10}No, this glyph doesn't mean "Cibola. " It means "the center of the world. "

655
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:03,830
你以前很喜欢这个的 她就是在寻宝的路途中爱上我的
{\fs10}You know, you used to like it. She fell in love with me on a treasure hunt.

656
00:48:03,870 --> 00:48:07,600
那不是爱情，是冲动，肾上腺素加上龙舌兰酒
{\fs10}That was not love. That was excitement, adrenaline and tequila.

657
00:48:07,670 --> 00:48:09,470
- 妈妈… - 我不过是想拿到学分而已
{\fs10}- Mom… - I was trying to get course credit.

658
00:48:09,540 --> 00:48:13,070
除非你最近不看书不读报 你该知道寻宝是有回报的
{\fs10}Treasure hunting paid off, in case you haven't read the papers.

659
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:15,300
但那跟你没什么关系，是本干的
{\fs10}Had nothing to do with you. That was Ben.

660
00:48:15,380 --> 00:48:17,680
本发现了宝藏，你什么都没干
{\fs10}Ben found the treasure. You did nothing.

661
00:48:17,750 --> 00:48:22,650
帕特里克，艾米丽，别吵了 我们专心解译古文吧？
{\fs10}Patrick, Emily, please. Can we just figure out what's on the page？

662
00:48:25,290 --> 00:48:26,950
就这么多了，恐怕帮不了你们
{\fs10}Well, that's it, I'm afraid.

663
00:48:27,660 --> 00:48:31,850
这些象形文字少了一部分 你们只拿到了一半藏宝图
{\fs10}These glyphs are only partials. So you only have half a treasure map.

664
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:34,260
我很遗憾
{\fs10}I'm sorry.

665
00:48:35,060 --> 00:48:37,030
我倒不是很惊讶
{\fs10}Not that I'm surprised.

666
00:48:38,600 --> 00:48:41,090
至少我们知道其余的部分在哪
{\fs10}At least we know where the rest of the map is.

667
00:48:41,740 --> 00:48:43,070
什么？
{\fs10}What？

668
00:48:43,570 --> 00:48:45,900
你知道在哪？那你为什么不告诉我
{\fs10}You know where it is？ Why didn't you tell me？

669
00:48:45,970 --> 00:48:48,640
原因很简单，你这个人容易反应过度
{\fs10}Obviously you have a tendency to overreact！

670
00:48:52,310 --> 00:48:55,220
- 对不起 - 我也是
{\fs10}- I'm sorry. - So am I.

671
00:48:55,280 --> 00:48:56,770
那究竟在哪儿呢？
{\fs10}So where is it？

672
00:48:56,890 --> 00:49:01,480
巴黎的雕像上铭写着 “双子坚定的屹立”
{\fs10}Inscription on the statue in Paris said, "These twins stand resolute. "

673
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:05,050
我们认为地图被分藏在两张坚定之桌内
{\fs10}We think the map's divided between the two Resolute desks.

674
00:49:05,130 --> 00:49:08,650
坚定之桌…就是那张坚定之桌？
{\fs10}The Resolute desk. The Resolute desk？

675
00:49:08,730 --> 00:49:10,630
总统的书桌？
{\fs10}President's desk？

676
00:49:11,270 --> 00:49:13,030
总统，什么总统？
{\fs10}The president. What president？

677
00:49:13,100 --> 00:49:16,040
- 是我们的总统么？ - 很不幸，就是他
{\fs10}- Our president？ - Unfortunately, yes.

678
00:49:16,110 --> 00:49:17,630
如此一来…
{\fs10}But that means…

679
00:49:17,710 --> 00:49:19,040
这么说，那我们就得…
{\fs10}Wait, so we have to…

680
00:49:20,340 --> 00:49:21,500
去白宫？
{\fs10}The White House？

681
00:49:22,850 --> 00:49:26,370
确切的说，是去总统办公室
{\fs10}The Oval Office… to be exact.

682
00:49:28,980 --> 00:49:30,780
我怎么可能会对这个反应过度呢？
{\fs10}Why would I overreact to that？

683
00:49:35,460 --> 00:49:39,290
- 我们事先约定的不是这个 - 请你专心处理眼前的问题好吗？
{\fs10}- That's not what I signed on for. - Could we focus on the issue at hand？

684
00:49:41,430 --> 00:49:42,420
谢谢
{\fs10}Thank you.

685
00:49:46,370 --> 00:49:48,360
年代很久远，早于哥伦布时期
{\fs10}It's early, pre-Columbian.

686
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:50,700
- 你能翻译吗？ - 别开玩笑了
{\fs10}- Can you translate it？ - Are you kidding？

687
00:49:50,770 --> 00:49:54,070
这是一种极其罕见的已经失传的语言
{\fs10}This is an extinct, exceedingly rare language.

688
00:49:54,140 --> 00:49:56,940
只有极少数一些人在研究这些语言
{\fs10}Only a handful of people study these languages.

689
00:49:57,010 --> 00:49:58,410
如何找到那些人？
{\fs10}Where are we to find them？

690
00:49:59,110 --> 00:50:02,480
在大学里也许能找到人 但你拿到的东西不完整
{\fs10}Universities, I suppose. But you don't have the whole thing.

691
00:50:02,550 --> 00:50:03,540
什么意思？
{\fs10}What do you mean？

692
00:50:04,290 --> 00:50:07,850
这些象形字被切断了
{\fs10}These glyphs here… they're cut off.

693
00:50:07,920 --> 00:50:11,090
还有其它地图？我们去哪找？
{\fs10}There's more to the map？ How are we going to find that？

694
00:50:11,090 --> 00:50:14,030
我们不用找，盖茨会去找的
{\fs10}We won't have to. Gates will get it somehow.

695
00:50:14,360 --> 00:50:18,770
坚定之桌的位置靠着总统办公室的南墙
{\fs10}The Resolute desk is near the south wall in the Oval Office.

696
00:50:18,830 --> 00:50:21,030
看这个，看
{\fs10}Look at this. Look.

697
00:50:21,100 --> 00:50:22,970
桌子的正面有扇小门
{\fs10}Small door on the front of the desk.

698
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:26,500
罗斯福装的，想遮掩他的轮椅
{\fs10}FDR had that put in so guests couldn't see his wheelchair.

699
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:29,480
- 但是… - 伙计们，看下这个
{\fs10}- But… - Guys, take a look at this.

700
00:50:31,310 --> 00:50:32,750
这也许能行
{\fs10}This could work.

701
00:50:32,810 --> 00:50:36,550
阿比盖尔，该和你的新男友来一次约会了
{\fs10}I believe it's time for you to make a date with your new boyfriend.

702
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:39,080
说的没错
{\fs10}I think you're right.

703
00:50:41,060 --> 00:50:45,620
欢迎参加白宫复活节滚蛋赛
{\fs10}We hope you're enjoying the White House Easter Egg Roll.

704
00:50:45,690 --> 00:50:49,790
两点钟在南边喷泉有脸谱彩绘
{\fs10}Face painting continues at 2:00 near the south fountain.

705
00:50:51,270 --> 00:50:54,830
- 那只大兔子是康纳扮的吗？ - 谢谢
{\fs10}- That Connor in the bunny suit？ - Thank you.

706
00:50:54,900 --> 00:50:58,030
我没参加过滚蛋赛，满有趣的
{\fs10}I've never been to an Easter Egg Roll. It's kind of sweet.

707
00:50:58,140 --> 00:50:59,770
嗯，我也很喜欢
{\fs10}Yeah, I love it.

708
00:51:01,310 --> 00:51:05,510
我认识你，你的曾曾祖父杀了林肯总统
{\fs10}I know you. Your great-great-grandfather killed President Lincoln.

709
00:51:05,580 --> 00:51:07,950
不，那是约翰・威尔克斯・布斯干的
{\fs10}No. That would be John Wilkes Booth.

710
00:51:08,020 --> 00:51:10,180
艾森施密尔说布斯是受人指使
{\fs10}Eisenschiml says that Booth was a tool

711
00:51:10,250 --> 00:51:13,690
这个惊天阴谋还牵涉到林肯的内阁成员
{\fs10}in a greater conspiracy that involved men in Lincoln's Cabinet.

712
00:51:13,760 --> 00:51:16,120
胡说！艾森施密尔的书里…
{\fs10}Absurd. Eisenschiml's book is filled with

713
00:51:16,190 --> 00:51:19,160
- 尽是些不实的研究和错误的假设 - 哦，是吗？
{\fs10}- spotty research and false assumptions. - Oh, yeah？

714
00:51:19,230 --> 00:51:22,360
那晚林肯的保镖擅离职守，怎么解释？
{\fs10}Explain why Lincoln's bodyguard left his post that night？

715
00:51:22,430 --> 00:51:25,830
因为林肯总统去戏院时从来不带保镖
{\fs10}Because President Lincoln was never accompanied by guards

