{\fs10}- Oh, wow. You are a lifesaver. - The Denby is great.

862
01:00:45,360 --> 01:00:48,560
不用考虑了，登比酒店刚刚被人订了 只剩弗农山庄了
{\fs10}Strike that. The Denby was booked. Mount Vernon's all we got.

863
01:00:48,630 --> 01:00:50,830
快订，别又让别人订了
{\fs10}Book it before someone else does.

864
01:00:55,540 --> 01:00:58,130
今天能来这儿是本人的莫大荣幸
{\fs10}And let me say what an honor it is to be here

865
01:00:58,240 --> 01:01:00,540
请允许我向总统先生说声，生日快乐
{\fs10}and add my happy birthday to you, Mr. President.

866
01:01:04,240 --> 01:01:05,540
弗吉尼亚  弗农山庄

867
01:01:30,940 --> 01:01:33,000
- 晚上好，先生 - 晚上好
{\fs10}- Good evening, sir. - Good evening.

868
01:01:33,070 --> 01:01:35,740
你知道这儿是管制区域吗？
{\fs10}Are you aware that you are in a restricted area？

869
01:01:35,810 --> 01:01:38,330
知道，但是这儿有鱼啊，年轻人
{\fs10}Yeah, but this is where the fish are, son.

870
01:01:38,410 --> 01:01:41,850
可能吧，但你得把船往上游开
{\fs10}That may be, but I'm gonna need to have you move upriver.

871
01:01:46,720 --> 01:01:50,050
你知道吗，根据马里兰州宪法第25章第1条
{\fs10}Are you aware that according to article one, section 25

872
01:01:50,120 --> 01:01:53,720
我有在公用水域钓鱼的权利
{\fs10}of the Maryland constitution, I'm allowed to fish in public water？

873
01:01:53,790 --> 01:01:58,660
你是否知道，我可以无条件拘留你48小时？
{\fs10}Are you aware I have the right to detain you for the next 48 hours without cause？

874
01:01:59,370 --> 01:02:03,800
我会尽快走人回家的
{\fs10}I am going to go back where I came from just as fast as possible.

875
01:02:11,210 --> 01:02:14,910
等到哪天我受邀参加酒会 说不定也会穿这一身衣服
{\fs10}Maybe one day I'll wear this thing to a party I was actually invited to.

876
01:02:24,690 --> 01:02:27,590
晚8点例检，11区请回话
{\fs10}Twenty hundred time check. Station 11.

877
01:02:27,660 --> 01:02:30,220
- 没有情况，周围安全 - 你好
{\fs10}- All clear. Perimeter secure. - Hey.

878
01:02:30,300 --> 01:02:33,630
你有没有看到附近有个可爱的褐发女子？
{\fs10}You didn't happen to see a cute brunette wandering around？

879
01:02:33,700 --> 01:02:36,790
- 我刚去拿了杯饮料，回来她就不见了 - 没有，先生
{\fs10}- Went to get a drink, she disappeared. - No, sir.

880
01:02:37,540 --> 01:02:39,030
今晚我要放空枪了
{\fs10}I've got no game tonight.

881
01:02:45,850 --> 01:02:49,940
晚上好，阁下…你好
{\fs10}Good evening, Your Excellency. Hello.

882
01:02:50,020 --> 01:02:54,040
首相大人，很高兴您又来美国了
{\fs10}Prime Minister, it's a delight to have you back in the States.

883
01:02:54,120 --> 01:02:58,250
宣传这个观点，竞选赞助限额 并不是强制执行的，因为总统…
{\fs10}Spread the word, contribution limits not enforced on the president's birth…

884
01:02:58,250 --> 01:02:59,810
- 生日快乐，总统先生 - 谢谢
{\fs10}- Happy birthday. - Thank you.

885
01:02:59,850 --> 01:03:03,580
- 我是本・盖茨，记得圣殿财宝么？ - 噢，是你啊，本・盖茨
{\fs10}- Ben Gates. The Templar treasure？ - Oh, right, Ben Gates. Yeah.

886
01:03:03,660 --> 01:03:06,920
- 我们就不占您的时间了 - 非常感谢
{\fs10}- We won't keep you. - Thanks so much. Always a pleasure.

887
01:03:06,990 --> 01:03:11,330
今晚能被邀来参加酒会，我兴奋得要命
{\fs10}I can't tell you what a thrill it is for me to be invited here tonight, sir.

888
01:03:11,400 --> 01:03:15,270
对，现在的你一定让情报机关忙到不行
{\fs10}Yeah, you must have the Secret Service hopping about now.

889
01:03:15,340 --> 01:03:16,670
您说什么？
{\fs10}Sir？

890
01:03:16,740 --> 01:03:18,800
因为你有了新的身世嘛
{\fs10}Considering your discovered lineage.

891
01:03:18,870 --> 01:03:21,400
- 噢，对，那个…… - 继续说吧
{\fs10}- Oh, yeah. Oh, that… - Carry on.

892
01:03:21,470 --> 01:03:24,670
对不起，先生，但是我知道你很崇拜华盛顿
{\fs10}I beg your pardon, sir, but I know what a huge admirer you are

893
01:03:24,740 --> 01:03:28,740
我觉得您该想看看这个
{\fs10}of George Washington. I thought you might want to take a look at this.

894
01:03:28,820 --> 01:03:30,370
看一下
{\fs10}Have a look at that.

895
01:03:30,450 --> 01:03:34,050
这是华盛顿亲手绘制的弗农山庄地图
{\fs10}This is a map of Mount Vernon drawn by George Washington himself.

896
01:03:34,120 --> 01:03:36,990
总统先生，您说的太对了
{\fs10}Mr. President, that is exactly what it is.

897
01:03:37,060 --> 01:03:40,820
- 耶鲁大学，建筑历史系 - 我不知道您是学这个的
{\fs10}- Architectural history major, Yale. - I did not know that.

898
01:03:40,890 --> 01:03:42,690
这是我叔祖父的
{\fs10}It belonged to my great uncle.

899
01:03:42,760 --> 01:03:44,890
原属于叫夏洛特的奴隶的孙女
{\fs10}Got it from the granddaughter of a slave, Charlotte.

900
01:03:44,960 --> 01:03:48,260
- 生日快乐，总统先生 - 非常感谢
{\fs10}- Happy birthday. - Always a pleasure. Thank you so much.

901
01:03:48,330 --> 01:03:51,900
夏洛特曾在弗农山庄工作生活过
{\fs10}Charlotte, who lived here and worked here at Mount Vernon.

902
01:03:51,970 --> 01:03:55,340
- 是啊 - 我们现正站在这个地方
{\fs10}- Yeah. - And we're standing right here, sir.

903
01:03:55,410 --> 01:03:59,670
这条线代表了一条地下通道 一条从未曾被人发现的逃生通道
{\fs10}This line is an underground tunnel, an escape route that was never found.

904
01:03:59,780 --> 01:04:03,410
不知道…不知道现在还在不在
{\fs10}I wonder… I wonder if it's still there.

905
01:04:04,420 --> 01:04:06,580
那么…
{\fs10}Well…

906
01:04:06,650 --> 01:04:10,350
- 要知道答案只有一种方法 - 不如我们去看看
{\fs10}- Only one way to find out, sir. - Maybe we should take a look.

907
01:04:11,120 --> 01:04:12,650
我们可以吗？
{\fs10}Are we allowed to do that？

908
01:04:13,030 --> 01:04:16,430
我知道您当然可以，您是总统
{\fs10}I mean, I know you're allowed to do that. You're the president.

909
01:04:16,500 --> 01:04:17,760
我能跟您一起去吗？
{\fs10}Can I come with you？

910
01:04:19,370 --> 01:04:22,060
- 你们真是无所不在啊 - 是，先生
{\fs10}- You guys are just everywhere. - Yes, sir.

911
01:04:22,140 --> 01:04:24,660
- 把手电给我的朋友 - 谢谢
{\fs10}- Give my friend your flashlight. - Thank you.

912
01:04:26,270 --> 01:04:28,540
根据地图，应该是…
{\fs10}According to this map, it should be…

913
01:04:29,610 --> 01:04:33,600
是一…二，在这儿
{\fs10}It's one… two. In here.

914
01:04:33,680 --> 01:04:35,310
对，应该是这儿
{\fs10}Yeah, should be in here.

915
01:04:37,080 --> 01:04:38,350
- 我可以进去吗？ - 当然
{\fs10}- May I？ - Absolutely.

916
01:04:38,420 --> 01:04:39,910
好
{\fs10}All right.

917
01:04:43,290 --> 01:04:46,730
克雷格，对你的工作我表示感激
{\fs10}You know, Craig, I appreciate you doing your job,

918
01:04:46,790 --> 01:04:48,780
但是这儿没有我的敌人
{\fs10}but I have no enemies down here.

919
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:52,620
在这个地下室，这个小房间里
{\fs10}In the cellar. In this tiny little room.

920
01:04:53,930 --> 01:04:55,400
那我就在这儿等吧
{\fs10}I'll just wait here, then.

921
01:05:06,350 --> 01:05:07,870
这边
{\fs10}Over here.

922
01:05:11,280 --> 01:05:15,150
- 那是乔治・华盛顿的标记 - 有点不一样
{\fs10}- That's the mark of George Washington. - Only it's slightly different.

923
01:05:15,220 --> 01:05:18,780
- 怎么不一样？ - 斧头的角度不一样
{\fs10}- How？ - These axes, the angle's off.

924
01:05:19,730 --> 01:05:25,560
根据地图上画的，应该是个完美的V字
{\fs10}For it to correspond with the ones on the map, it should form a perfect V.

925
01:05:31,770 --> 01:05:32,970
好，还有什么
{\fs10}OK, what else？

926
01:05:33,910 --> 01:05:35,810
箭头…
{\fs10}The arrowhead…

927
01:05:38,310 --> 01:05:40,070
偏到一边了
{\fs10}…is sideways.

928
01:05:47,820 --> 01:05:49,880
我们很好，别担心
{\fs10}We're all right. Don't worry.

929
01:05:55,290 --> 01:05:56,590
看看
{\fs10}Look at that.

930
01:05:57,400 --> 01:05:58,390
来吧
{\fs10}Come on.

931
01:06:04,640 --> 01:06:05,630
总统先生？
{\fs10}Mr. President？

932
01:06:07,210 --> 01:06:09,770
9区有情况！
{\fs10}We have a breach in zone nine！ There's…

933
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:16,180
- 通知费尔法克斯郡政府 - 周边通报情况，封锁所有出口
{\fs10}- Inform Fairfax, SecTac Channel One！ - Perimeter detail, lock down all exits！

934
01:06:16,850 --> 01:06:19,820
- 盖茨，你在干什么 - 对不起，总统先生
{\fs10}- Gates, what are you doing？ - I'm sorry, Mr. President.

935
01:06:19,890 --> 01:06:24,120
我必须问您个问题，但我知道 只有我们俩独处时您才会回答
{\fs10}I need to ask you a question, which I know you can't answer unless we're alone.

936
01:06:24,190 --> 01:06:26,490
我们两个进来了！
{\fs10}Two coming in！

937
01:06:27,260 --> 01:06:30,750
我要一把锤子，一把铁撬 还要一台凿石机
{\fs10}I want a sledgehammer, I want a crowbar, I want a jackhammer, now！

938
01:06:32,300 --> 01:06:34,290
汤姆，通知副总统
{\fs10}Tom, alert the vice president.

939
01:06:35,500 --> 01:06:38,100
总统先生，1880年至今
{\fs10}Mr. President, sometime between 1880,

940
01:06:38,170 --> 01:06:41,270
坚定之桌搬入总统办公室后
{\fs10}when the Resolute desk was placed in the Oval Office,

941
01:06:41,340 --> 01:06:45,830
我国有一位总统发现书桌里的秘密夹层
{\fs10}and now, one of our presidents found a secret compartment in the desk.

942
01:06:45,910 --> 01:06:49,680
夹层里有一块写有 印第安人土著文字的木板
{\fs10}Hidden inside was a plank with Native American writing on it.

943
01:06:49,750 --> 01:06:54,520
那是传说中的黄金城――锡沃拉的藏宝图
{\fs10}A treasure map to Cibola, the legendary City of Gold, sir.

944
01:06:54,590 --> 01:06:56,920
你千辛万苦，只是想问我藏宝图？
{\fs10}All this just to ask me about a treasure map？

945
01:06:57,020 --> 01:07:00,390
藏宝图是证明托马斯・盖茨清白的关键
{\fs10}That map is a key to proving Thomas Gates' innocence.

946
01:07:00,430 --> 01:07:04,690
我知道那木板已经不在坚定之桌里了
{\fs10}I know for a fact that the plank is no longer in the Resolute desk.

947
01:07:04,760 --> 01:07:06,290
你已经拜访过我的桌子了？
{\fs10}You've been in my desk too？

948
01:07:06,370 --> 01:07:09,430
我知道那块木板的下落
{\fs10}I believe the whereabouts of that plank is now hidden…

949
01:07:10,270 --> 01:07:12,290
就藏在总统秘卷中
{\fs10}…in the President's Book, sir.

950
01:07:15,240 --> 01:07:17,300
那秘卷只有总统才能看
{\fs10}The book known only to our presidents.

951
01:07:18,410 --> 01:07:20,900
秘卷里有所有的国家机密
{\fs10}It contains all of our nation's secrets.

952
01:07:25,720 --> 01:07:28,450
我从没听过比这更荒唐的事情
{\fs10}That's the most ridiculous thing I've ever heard.

953
01:07:28,520 --> 01:07:34,390
我看过书桌里的徽章 这说明地图的确存在
{\fs10}I saw the seal in the desk, sir. I know the map exists.

954
01:07:35,960 --> 01:07:38,450
你不打算告诉我怎么出去…
{\fs10}You're not going to tell me how to get out of here

955
01:07:38,530 --> 01:07:41,900
- 除非你达到目的 - 出去的路就往那边走
{\fs10}- unless you get what you want. - The way out is that direction,

956
01:07:41,970 --> 01:07:43,800
我会带您出去的
{\fs10}and I'll show you.

957
01:07:43,870 --> 01:07:45,930
你不太会谈判，对吧？
{\fs10}You don't negotiate very well, do you？

958
01:07:46,970 --> 01:07:48,200
不懂，先生
{\fs10}No, sir.

959
01:07:48,840 --> 01:07:50,000
总统先生？
{\fs10}Mr. President！

960
01:07:50,080 --> 01:07:51,770
我要的锤子呢？
{\fs10}Where are my sledgehammers？

961
01:07:57,650 --> 01:07:58,910
我不明白，盖茨
{\fs10}I don't get you, Gates.

962
01:07:59,050 --> 01:08:01,820
你这么做，甚至为此甘愿去坐牢
{\fs10}You do all this, you're willing to go to prison,

963
01:08:01,890 --> 01:08:04,190
就为了洗刷你祖先的名声
{\fs10}just to clear your ancestor's name.

964
01:08:04,890 --> 01:08:07,320
走下阶梯就能出去
{\fs10}The way out is just down those stairs.

965
01:08:08,530 --> 01:08:11,500
没有先人，就没有现在的我
{\fs10}Everything I am is because of my ancestors, sir.

966
01:08:12,300 --> 01:08:15,060
托马斯・盖茨对他的祖国献出满腔热血
{\fs10}Thomas Gates gave his last full measure of devotion

967
01:08:15,130 --> 01:08:17,730
以阻止金环骑士会的阴谋
{\fs10}to his country to stop the KGC.

968
01:08:17,800 --> 01:08:21,600
当一个人为国捐躯时 我相信他该受到赞扬
{\fs10}When someone dies for their country, I believe they should be honored.

969
01:08:21,670 --> 01:08:23,540
“献出满腔热血？”
{\fs10}"Last full measure of devotion"？

970
01:08:24,210 --> 01:08:27,080
林肯是我最喜欢的总统 我没有冒犯您的意思
{\fs10}Lincoln is my favorite president, sir. No offense.

971
01:08:28,310 --> 01:08:31,650
没关系，他也是我心中的英雄
{\fs10}None taken. He's my favorite too.

972
01:08:33,450 --> 01:08:36,650
我知道有这本书，问题是…
{\fs10}Sir, I know the book exists, and my question is,

973
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:40,090
能否同意让我一观？
{\fs10}"Will you agree to let me see it？"

974
01:08:40,730 --> 01:08:43,420
如果那种东西真的存在
{\fs10}Even if something like that really did exist,

975
01:08:43,500 --> 01:08:46,400
凭什么认为我会给你看？
{\fs10}why do you think I would actually just give it to you？

976
01:08:47,000 --> 01:08:48,860
因为这可能会指引我们
{\fs10}Because it will probably lead us

977
01:08:48,930 --> 01:08:53,030
发现史上最大的印第安宝藏
{\fs10}to the discovery of the greatest Native American treasure of all time.

978
01:08:53,670 --> 01:08:56,670
一块巨大的文化空白
{\fs10}A huge piece of culture lost.

979
01:08:56,780 --> 01:08:59,840
你可以将那段历史交还给它的后代们
{\fs10}You can give that history back to its descendants.

980
01:08:59,880 --> 01:09:04,080
而且因为您是美国总统，先生
{\fs10}And because you're the president of the United States, sir.

981
01:09:04,150 --> 01:09:09,020
无论是您内在的人格，捍卫宪法的誓言
{\fs10}Whether by innate character, or the oath you took to defend the Constitution,

982
01:09:09,090 --> 01:09:11,990
还是肩头的历史重任，您都会这么做的
{\fs10}or the weight of history that falls upon you.

983
01:09:12,660 --> 01:09:15,590
我相信您是位可敬的人，先生
{\fs10}I believe you to be an honorable man, sir.

984
01:09:17,630 --> 01:09:20,000
人民已经不相信这些东西了
{\fs10}People don't believe that stuff anymore.

985
01:09:22,000 --> 01:09:23,530
他们愿意相信
{\fs10}They want to believe it.

986
01:09:45,730 --> 01:09:50,560
最近的公路在那边，恕我无法与您同路了
{\fs10}Nearest highway is that direction. You'll understand if we part ways here.

987
01:09:55,530 --> 01:09:57,930
- 盖茨 - 先生
{\fs10}- Gates. - Sir？

988
01:09:58,000 --> 01:10:01,060
我下面要讲的话，你就当从没听过
{\fs10}The following conversation never happened.

989
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:03,910
那本书的确存在
{\fs10}The book exists.

990
01:10:05,080 --> 01:10:07,510
- 在哪里？ - 你会把书放在哪里？
{\fs10}- Where is it？ - Where else do you keep a book？

991
01:10:07,580 --> 01:10:09,410
就在国会图书馆
{\fs10}In the Library of Congress.

992
01:10:10,150 --> 01:10:14,850
X，Y，2，3，4，7，8，6
{\fs10}X, Y, two, three, four, seven, eight, six.

993
01:10:15,190 --> 01:10:16,210
谢谢你，先生
{\fs10}Thank you, sir.

994
01:10:17,190 --> 01:10:22,090
还得记住3，7，9，4
{\fs10}You'll also need to know three, seven, nine, four.

995
01:10:22,160 --> 01:10:23,460
知道了
{\fs10}Got it.

996
01:10:24,530 --> 01:10:28,160
- 盖茨 - 先生
{\fs10}- And, Gates… - Sir？

997
01:10:28,700 --> 01:10:33,540
有两百人知道你绑架了我 我无法告诉他们原因
{\fs10}Two hundred people know you held me against my will. I can't tell them why.

998
01:10:33,610 --> 01:10:35,940
除非你找到你需要的东西
{\fs10}Unless you find what you're looking for,

999
01:10:36,010 --> 01:10:38,810
你会被控绑架总统的罪名
{\fs10}you'll be charged with kidnapping the president.

1000
01:10:38,880 --> 01:10:43,250
- 你知道那意味着什么 - 是的，非常清楚
{\fs10}- You know what that means. - Yes, sir. Very much so, sir.

1001
01:10:47,120 --> 01:10:50,780
- 我要你帮我做件事 - 这是我的荣幸
{\fs10}- I want you to do something for me. - It would be a privilege, sir.

1002
01:10:51,660 --> 01:10:55,680
第47页，好好看看
{\fs10}Page 47. Just have a look at that.

1003
01:10:58,930 --> 01:11:02,130
莱利，国会图书馆，20分钟后见
{\fs10}Riley, meet me at the Library of Congress in 20 minutes.

1004
01:11:04,840 --> 01:11:05,830
好
{\fs10}OK.

1005
01:11:13,110 --> 01:11:14,100
我是萨德斯基
{\fs10}Sadusky.

1006
01:11:16,780 --> 01:11:19,650
总统他…怎么了？
{\fs10}The president's been what？

1007
01:11:22,020 --> 01:11:23,010
是盖茨
{\fs10}Gates.

1008
01:11:28,090 --> 01:11:30,620
XY234786
{\fs10}X- Y-two-three-four-seven-eight-six.

1009
01:11:30,700 --> 01:11:35,100
XY234786…XY234786…
{\fs10}X- Y-two-three-four-seven-eight-six. X- Y-two-three-four-seven-eight-six.

1010
01:11:35,170 --> 01:11:36,790
- 嘿 - 你好
{\fs10}- Hey. - Hey.

1011
01:11:37,200 --> 01:11:38,570
谜底就在眼前
{\fs10}We're close.

1012
01:11:48,650 --> 01:11:52,140
- 我们从哪儿开始？ - XY是图书分类号
{\fs10}- Where do we start？ - XY is the book classification code.

1013
01:11:52,220 --> 01:11:55,710
XY代表特别类，就是非常珍贵的书籍
{\fs10}Stands for special collections, which means very special books.

1014
01:11:55,790 --> 01:11:58,760
- 这些书在哪儿？ - 这边走，我们得偷偷溜进去
{\fs10}- Where are they？ - This way. We'll sneak in.

1015
01:12:21,710 --> 01:12:22,700
这下好了
{\fs10}This will be good.

1016
01:12:25,650 --> 01:12:28,140
到了，XA…XM…
{\fs10}Here we go. XA… XM…

1017
01:12:34,130 --> 01:12:36,590
看这儿，你有密码吗？
{\fs10}Look. Do you have a code？

1018
01:12:37,630 --> 01:12:39,090
3-7-9-4
{\fs10}Three-seven-nine-four.

1019
01:12:46,470 --> 01:12:48,770
总统说书目号是多少？
{\fs10}What did the president say the number was？

1020
01:12:48,970 --> 01:12:50,070
是234786
{\fs10}Two-three-four-seven-eight-six.

1021
01:12:59,120 --> 01:13:01,140
2-3-6-7…
{\fs10}Two-three-six-seven…

1022
01:13:01,220 --> 01:13:04,280
XY233，2378…在这儿
{\fs10}X- Y-two-three-three, two-three-seven-eight… Here.

1023
01:13:04,350 --> 01:13:08,990
- 23479… - 78…
{\fs10}- Two-three-four-seven-nine… - Seventy-six, 78…

1024
01:13:09,060 --> 01:13:10,360
不在这里
{\fs10}It's not there.

1025
01:13:12,300 --> 01:13:14,960
可能有人借出去了
{\fs10}Maybe someone checked it out.

1026
01:13:16,600 --> 01:13:20,770
- 既然没书，他为什么叫我们来？ - 也许他是想让我们被捕
{\fs10}- Why send us here if there's no book？ - He probably wanted us to get caught.

1027
01:13:30,580 --> 01:13:31,570
看这儿
{\fs10}Here.

1028
01:13:48,130 --> 01:13:51,000
- 什么东西 - 六位数字锁
{\fs10}- What is that？ - It's a six-dial combination lock.

1029
01:13:53,070 --> 01:13:54,970
书目号就是密码
{\fs10}The location is the combination.

1030
01:13:56,310 --> 01:13:58,110
书目号就是密码…
{\fs10}The location is the combination.

1031
01:14:15,260 --> 01:14:17,230
我说的没错吧
{\fs10}Yes. I was right.

1032
01:14:18,130 --> 01:14:19,530
干得好，普尔先生
{\fs10}Well done, Mr. Poole.

1033
01:14:26,710 --> 01:14:28,300
鹰和卷轴
{\fs10}Eagle and the scroll.

1034
01:14:41,090 --> 01:14:42,610
- 51区… - 嘘！
{\fs10}- Area 51！ - Shh！

1035
01:14:45,760 --> 01:14:48,250
- 是肯尼迪刺杀案… - 嘘！没时间看这些
{\fs10}- Kennedy assassination. - Shh！ We don't have time.

1036
01:14:48,330 --> 01:14:50,350
对，那倒是真的
{\fs10}Yeah, it's true.

1037
01:14:53,370 --> 01:14:56,030
这个，等等
{\fs10}Here. Wait.

1038
01:14:56,100 --> 01:15:00,270
1865年4月，维多利亚女王给派克发了两封密码信函
{\fs10}"April 1865. Queen Victoria sends Pike two coded missives.

1039
01:15:00,370 --> 01:15:04,810
第一封信打开后，里面的信息…
{\fs10}The first is received. Contains information regarding

1040
01:15:04,840 --> 01:15:08,280
是有关新大陆宝藏的，黄金之城！
{\fs10}New World treasure. The City of Gold. "

1041
01:15:08,880 --> 01:15:12,250
等等，女王想要帮南部邦联的忙？
{\fs10}Wait. The queen wanted to help the Confederacy？

1042
01:15:12,320 --> 01:15:15,950
- 分裂的美国更容易对付 - 英国需要南方的棉花
{\fs10}- A divided America'd have been weaker. - Needed cotton from the South.

1043
01:15:16,020 --> 01:15:19,180
第二封信据信写有普莱费厄密码
{\fs10}"The second missive was thought to contain a Playfair cipher

1044
01:15:19,260 --> 01:15:23,190
建议与拉布莱伊联系 他死前会将线索埋藏起来
{\fs10}suggesting contact with Laboulaye, who'll hide clues before his death. "

1045
01:15:23,260 --> 01:15:26,990
那就是布斯日记里写的密码 也是托马斯想烧掉的
{\fs10}The cipher written into the Booth diary page that Thomas tried to burn.

1046
01:15:27,070 --> 01:15:29,360
- 就是我们发现的那个 - 没错，1880年…
{\fs10}- The one we have. - Exactly. "1880.

1047
01:15:30,140 --> 01:15:34,330
坚定之桌抵达华盛顿 作为女王送给海斯总统的礼物
{\fs10}Resolute desk arrives in Washington, sent by queen to President Hayes. "

1048
01:15:36,380 --> 01:15:37,360
看这个
{\fs10}Look at that.

1049
01:15:39,140 --> 01:15:42,410
白宫失踪的木板，哇哦
{\fs10}Missing plank from the White House. Wow.

1050
01:15:44,380 --> 01:15:46,940
最后一条是柯立芝总统写的
{\fs10}Here's the final entry by President Coolidge.

1051
01:15:47,020 --> 01:15:51,080
1924年，我在书桌秘密夹层发现一块板子
{\fs10}"1924. I found a plank in secret desk compartment.

1052
01:15:51,160 --> 01:15:54,850
留下照片后，木板被摧毁
{\fs10}Plank photographed and then destroyed.

1053
01:15:54,930 --> 01:15:57,730
并委派博格鲁姆去摧毁地标
{\fs10}Borglum commissioned to destroy landmarks

1054
01:15:57,830 --> 01:15:59,920
地点在神圣的黑岗山
{\fs10}in sacred Black Hills mountains. "

1055
01:16:02,530 --> 01:16:06,160
博格鲁姆？和拉什莫尔山有关系嘛？{\fs12}（拉什莫尔山：即著名的总统山，刻有4名总统的头像）
{\fs10}Borglum. Mount Rushmore？

1056
01:16:06,840 --> 01:16:11,830
他在拉什莫尔山上雕刻 是为了抹去地图上的地标
{\fs10}He carved Mount Rushmore to erase the map's landmarks

1057
01:16:11,910 --> 01:16:14,380
从而保护黄金之城
{\fs10}in order to protect the City of Gold.

1058
01:16:15,410 --> 01:16:18,040
拉什莫尔山竟然是个幌子
{\fs10}Mount Rushmore was a cover-up.

1059
01:16:18,120 --> 01:16:20,880
什么声音？
{\fs10}What is it？

1060
01:16:22,450 --> 01:16:25,860
那些领我税金的家伙要来捉我了
{\fs10}There's my tax dollars at work, coming to arrest me.

1061
01:16:25,920 --> 01:16:28,550
他们是来捉我的，快去开车
{\fs10}Not coming for you, they're for me. Go to the car.

1062
01:16:28,630 --> 01:16:30,530
- 不 - 快去，我会同你们会合的
{\fs10}- No！ - Go！ I'll meet up with you.

1063
01:16:31,100 --> 01:16:32,090
往这儿走
{\fs10}This way.

1064
01:16:40,940 --> 01:16:43,340
盖茨先是绑架了总统，然后又放了他
{\fs10}So Gates abducts the president, lets him go

1065
01:16:43,410 --> 01:16:45,400
随后就来到了国会图书馆？
{\fs10}and heads to the Library of Congress？

1066
01:16:45,480 --> 01:16:48,110
- 为什么？ - 可能他想借本书看看
{\fs10}- Why？ - Maybe he wants to check out a book.

1067
01:17:07,530 --> 01:17:09,090
这边
{\fs10}This way.

1068
01:17:29,990 --> 01:17:32,460
所有探员注意…
{\fs10}All agents…

1069
01:17:45,170 --> 01:17:47,000
- 爸爸 - 本
{\fs10}- Dad. - Ben.

1070
01:17:47,070 --> 01:17:49,340
快点出来，我得把车开走了
{\fs10}Get out of there. I had to move the car.

1071
01:17:49,410 --> 01:17:51,810
满大街都是FBI和特勤局的人
{\fs10}FBI, Secret Service all over the place.

1072
01:17:51,880 --> 01:17:54,640
别慌，我先把木板的照片发到你手机上
{\fs10}Calm down. I sent a picture of the plank to your cell.

1073
01:17:54,710 --> 01:17:56,650
- 你能把照片发过来？ - 对，我能
{\fs10}- You can do that？ - Yes, I can do that.

1074
01:17:56,750 --> 01:17:58,380
收到照片了吗？
{\fs10}Did you get it？

1075
01:17:59,180 --> 01:18:00,520
- 收到了 - 看
{\fs10}- I got it. - Look.

1076
01:18:02,220 --> 01:18:06,280
- 拿去给妈妈翻译 - 为什么让我去？
{\fs10}- Take it to Mom for translation. - Why me？

1077
01:18:06,360 --> 01:18:08,420
他说他妈妈可以翻译木板？
{\fs10}He say his mom could translate the plank？

1078
01:18:08,490 --> 01:18:10,390
查查她的底细
{\fs10}Find out who she is.

1079
01:18:21,610 --> 01:18:24,340
- 我们怎么去找本？ - 不知道
{\fs10}- How are we going to find Ben？ - I don't know.

1080
01:18:24,410 --> 01:18:26,310
- 站住！你们是谁？ - 我们是工作人员
{\fs10}- Hold it！ Who are you？ - We work here.

1081
01:18:26,380 --> 01:18:28,570
- 身份卡 - 拿去，有人叫我们疏散
{\fs10}- IDs. - Here. We were told to evacuate.

1082
01:18:28,650 --> 01:18:30,340
我不知道里面发生了什么事
{\fs10}I don't know what's going on.

1083
01:18:30,420 --> 01:18:33,010
- 我的车停在… - 前一秒我还在看书…
{\fs10}- My car's parked… - One second I'm reading…

1084
01:18:33,090 --> 01:18:36,580
- 一个特别的区域… - 转眼间就被赶了出来…
{\fs10}- Special section for… … a book, then we're rushed out…

1085
01:18:36,660 --> 01:18:38,210
- 走吧 - 谢谢
{\fs10}- Go ahead. - OK. Thank you.

1086
01:18:38,290 --> 01:18:41,380
- 遇见人最好拿出身份卡，祝你们好运 - 多谢你的帮助，警官
{\fs10}- Thank you for your help, officer. - Best of luck.

1087
01:18:41,890 --> 01:18:44,690
晚安
{\fs10}Have a good night.

1088
01:18:48,300 --> 01:18:51,530
到东北区去…
{\fs10}Hey, go to the northeast sectors…

1089
01:18:55,010 --> 01:18:56,340
发动引擎
{\fs10}Start the car.

1090
01:18:59,410 --> 01:19:00,570
挂好排档
{\fs10}Put it in gear.

1091
01:19:02,580 --> 01:19:04,520
怎么回事？
{\fs10}- Uh-oh. - What's the problem？

1092
01:19:04,580 --> 01:19:05,710
没问题，快开车
{\fs10}It's clear. Let's go！

1093
01:19:06,320 --> 01:19:07,620
我们会坐牢的
{\fs10}We're going to jail.

1094
01:19:10,720 --> 01:19:12,490
我要检查一下…
{\fs10}I want to run a check…

1095
01:19:15,390 --> 01:19:16,690
进来，抓稳
{\fs10}Get in！ Hang on！

1096
01:19:18,300 --> 01:19:19,530
一辆奔驰SUV…
{\fs10}Mercedes SUV…

1097
01:19:19,600 --> 01:19:22,160
- 他上来了，快开车！ - 抓稳了！
{\fs10}- He's in！ Go！ - Hang on！

1098
01:19:25,140 --> 01:19:26,230
好，我们能行的
{\fs10}OK. We can do this.

1099
01:19:30,440 --> 01:19:32,570
升起路障，封住出口！
{\fs10}Close the barricade, lock it down！

1100
01:19:32,640 --> 01:19:34,740
封住出口！
{\fs10}Lock it down！

1101
01:19:37,450 --> 01:19:39,280
- 快开，快开 - 好
{\fs10}- Drive, drive, drive！ - OK.

1102
01:19:41,450 --> 01:19:43,110
不行！
{\fs10}I don't think so！

1103
01:19:49,490 --> 01:19:51,830
快！快！快！
{\fs10}Go, go, go, go, go！

1104
01:19:51,900 --> 01:19:54,160
快走！快点！
{\fs10}Let's go！ Let's go！

1105
01:19:56,740 --> 01:19:59,230
这跟计划中的不一样！
{\fs10}That did not turn out the way it was supposed to！

1106
01:19:59,300 --> 01:20:01,970
- 他们怎么这么快就找到我们了？ - 我来告诉你是怎么回事
{\fs10}- How'd they find us so quick？ - I'll tell you how.

1107
01:20:02,040 --> 01:20:05,700
- 总统他打了小报告！ - 是萨德斯基，刚才在图书馆见到他了
{\fs10}- The president is a tattletale！ - Sadusky. He was there.

1108
01:20:05,780 --> 01:20:08,110
关于那本书，看来他知道不少
{\fs10}He knows more about the book than I thought.

1109
01:20:08,180 --> 01:20:10,870
被人绑架，总统先生他感觉如何啊？
{\fs10}How'd the president feel about being kidnapped？

1110
01:20:11,450 --> 01:20:12,540
还行吧
{\fs10}He was OK.

1111
01:20:18,960 --> 01:20:21,890
- 阿普尔顿博士 - 办公室已经关门了，不好意思
{\fs10}- Dr. Appleton. - This office is closed. I'm sorry.

1112
01:20:21,960 --> 01:20:24,430
抱歉这么晚打扰
{\fs10}I do apologize for the lateness of the hour.

1113
01:20:25,800 --> 01:20:27,990
我的名字是米奇・威尔金森
{\fs10}My name is Mitch Wilkinson.

1114
01:20:28,070 --> 01:20:31,700
我想让你看个东西，很快就好
{\fs10}I've got something I want you to take a look at. Just take a minute.

1115
01:20:39,480 --> 01:20:41,780
- 你是宝藏猎人 - 不，女士
{\fs10}- You're a treasure hunter. - No, ma'am.

1116
01:20:41,850 --> 01:20:44,610
我只是一个想青史留名的人
{\fs10}I'm just a man trying to make his mark on history.

1117
01:20:45,150 --> 01:20:46,480
能帮我吗？
{\fs10}Can you help me？

1118
01:20:47,890 --> 01:20:52,150
我不懂那种语言，抱歉，帮不上忙
{\fs10}Um… No, I don't know that language. I'm sorry. I can't help you.

1119
01:20:52,260 --> 01:20:54,780
请原谅
{\fs10}Oh, excuse me.

1120
01:20:57,930 --> 01:20:59,020
对
{\fs10}Yes.

1121
01:21:00,630 --> 01:21:02,100
知道了
{\fs10}Got it.

1122
01:21:02,700 --> 01:21:06,470
你的前夫正在路上，他也想要你的翻译
{\fs10}Your ex-husband's on his way up. He wants the translation.

1123
01:21:07,910 --> 01:21:13,070
不许告诉他真相，甩开他 否则他的命就难保了
{\fs10}Tell him anything but the truth. Get rid of him. His life depends on it.

1124
01:21:22,720 --> 01:21:24,280
艾米丽？
{\fs10}Emily？

1125
01:21:37,000 --> 01:21:39,230
我知道你最不想见的人就是我
{\fs10}I know I'm the last person you want to see,

1126
01:21:39,310 --> 01:21:44,570
我也觉得很别扭，但我们需要你翻译点东西
{\fs10}and I'm not comfortable either, but we need you to translate something.

1127
01:21:46,350 --> 01:21:50,580
- 本让我来的，他需要你帮忙 - 那没问题
{\fs10}- Ben sent me. He needs your help. - Yes, of course.

1128
01:21:51,890 --> 01:21:53,880
如果是本，就没问题，是什么东西？
{\fs10}If it's for Ben, of course. What is it？

1129
01:21:57,360 --> 01:22:00,120
在手机里，我不知道怎么…
{\fs10}It's in the cell phone. I'm not sure how to…

1130
01:22:00,190 --> 01:22:02,180
- 给我 - …把图片调出来
{\fs10}- Give it to me. … bring it out.

1131
01:22:10,070 --> 01:22:12,470
我们知道这地方应该在拉什莫尔山附近
{\fs10}We know it leads to Mount Rushmore.

1132
01:22:16,540 --> 01:22:19,740
对，“岛…草之海中，石之岛耸”
{\fs10}Yes. "Islands… Islands of stone in a sea of grass. "

1133
01:22:19,810 --> 01:22:24,440
那是拉科塔土著用来称呼 南达科他州的黑岗山
{\fs10}That's what the Lakota used to call the Black Hills in South Dakota.

1134
01:22:25,150 --> 01:22:26,140
嗯
{\fs10}Right.

1135
01:22:29,420 --> 01:22:33,830
“月侵地处，蜂鸟翼舒”
{\fs10}"Find where the moon touches the earth and release the hummingbird. "

1136
01:22:38,400 --> 01:22:39,460
只有这些？
{\fs10}That's it？

1137
01:22:47,070 --> 01:22:51,410
你有没有想过…？没想到我会说出来
{\fs10}Did it ever occur to you？ I can't believe I'm saying this.

1138
01:22:52,610 --> 01:22:56,550
你有没有想过 我做那些事是为了引你注意？
{\fs10}Did it ever occur to you that I did the things I did to impress you？

1139
01:22:59,320 --> 01:23:03,190
不，你只是自己想做，而我也会做同样的事
{\fs10}No, you did it because you wanted to, and I would've done the same thing,

1140
01:23:03,260 --> 01:23:06,590
只是我们有人得负责养家育儿
{\fs10}except one of us had to grow up and stay home and look after Ben.

1141
01:23:06,660 --> 01:23:08,650
当然那绝对不是你
{\fs10}Certainly wasn't going to be you.

1142
01:23:09,530 --> 01:23:13,990
你有没有想过，是我做出你做不来的牺牲？
{\fs10}Did it ever occur to you that I made sacrifices for us that you never did？

1143
01:23:16,600 --> 01:23:18,160
肯定没有
{\fs10}No, of course not.

1144
01:23:18,640 --> 01:23:20,470
你还是走吧
{\fs10}So just go away.

1145
01:23:34,550 --> 01:23:36,040
可恶的龙舌兰酒
{\fs10}Lousy tequila.

1146
01:23:40,630 --> 01:23:42,860
别再沮丧了，你做得很好
{\fs10}Don't feel bad. You did good.

1147
01:23:42,930 --> 01:23:44,990
帕特里克对你的话深信不疑
{\fs10}Patrick believed every word you said.

1148
01:23:45,070 --> 01:23:48,630
而且，你儿子他找不到宝藏的
{\fs10}Besides, your son would have never found the treasure anyway.

1149
01:23:48,700 --> 01:23:50,530
你不了解本杰明
{\fs10}You don't know Benjamin.

1150
01:23:50,600 --> 01:23:54,170
也许我不了解，但是我有这个
{\fs10}Perhaps not. But then again, I have this.

1151
01:23:57,810 --> 01:24:02,680
维多利亚女王写给南军将领派克的信？
{\fs10}A letter from Queen Victoria to the Confederate General Albert Pike？

1152
01:24:02,750 --> 01:24:07,020
我们的女王似乎更偏爱南部邦联
{\fs10}Seems the dear old queen was partial to the Confederate cause.

1153
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:10,660
这封信在我的家族中已经传承了140年
{\fs10}This has been handed down by my family for 140 years.

1154
01:24:11,490 --> 01:24:15,790
里面有最重要的信息，也是最后的线索
{\fs10}Contains a vital piece of information. The final clue, as it were.

1155
01:24:15,860 --> 01:24:21,730
若没有你的翻译，这条信息毫无价值
{\fs10}This piece of information is worthless without your translation of the planks.

1156
01:24:23,240 --> 01:24:25,000
真是讽刺啊
{\fs10}It's ironic, isn't it？

1157
01:24:25,070 --> 01:24:29,840
一切都从烧毁一页纸开始
{\fs10}This all began with the burning of pages, and now it ends

1158
01:24:29,910 --> 01:24:33,440
结局却是烧毁这个最终的线索
{\fs10}with the burning of this, the final clue.

1159
01:24:34,280 --> 01:24:36,010
让我成为唯一
{\fs10}Making me the only one…

1160
01:24:37,220 --> 01:24:38,710
能找到锡沃拉的人
{\fs10}…who can find Cibola.

1161
01:24:40,990 --> 01:24:42,050
带上外套
{\fs10}Get your coat.

1162
01:24:54,940 --> 01:24:57,930
就她对第二块板子的翻译来看
{\fs10}Her translation on the second half of the planks says

1163
01:24:58,000 --> 01:25:01,570
- 我们要找的是一个石之岛 - 本应该已经找到了
{\fs10}- we need to find an island of stone. - Ben would have found it by now.

1164
01:25:01,980 --> 01:25:03,240
我不这么认为
{\fs10}I don't think so.

1165
01:25:11,050 --> 01:25:12,880
怎么才能到这里…
{\fs10}How do I get to, um, this…

1166
01:25:14,750 --> 01:25:15,980
你好，米奇
{\fs10}Hello, Mitch.

1167
01:25:17,660 --> 01:25:18,720
妈妈…
{\fs10}Mom…

1168
01:25:18,790 --> 01:25:21,660
- 等我一下 - 没门，你太慢啦
{\fs10}- Wait for me. - No way. You're too slow.

1169
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:24,990
我跟你爸说的那些话，我就知道你能明白的
{\fs10}I knew you'd figure out the message I gave your father.

1170
01:25:25,400 --> 01:25:28,370
“蜂鸟”这谜语真不错…放了她，米奇{\fs12}（关于蜂鸟之谜的猜测，请看片尾字幕）
{\fs10}The hummingbird was good. Let her go.

1171
01:25:28,440 --> 01:25:32,170
枪在我们手上，轮不到你发号施令
{\fs10}We're the ones with the firepower, and you're giving me orders.

1172
01:25:32,240 --> 01:25:36,510
我绑架了总统，FBI现在正抓我呢
{\fs10}I kidnapped the president. The FBI is on their way right now to arrest me,

1173
01:25:36,580 --> 01:25:38,600
相信他们见到你会很高兴的
{\fs10}and I'm sure they'll love to meet you.

1174
01:25:38,680 --> 01:25:40,810
他们会找到我们两个，然后拿出两付手铐
{\fs10}They'll find us both and arrest us both.

1175
01:25:40,880 --> 01:25:43,610
顺着那条路可没法走到黄金之城，对吧？
{\fs10}That path doesn't lead to the City of Gold, does it？

1176
01:25:43,850 --> 01:25:46,750
这个人身上有你需要的线索，他有封信
{\fs10}This man has information you need. He's got a letter.

1177
01:25:46,820 --> 01:25:49,190
维多利亚女王给阿尔伯特・派克将军的信
{\fs10}From Queen Victoria to General Albert Pike.

1178
01:25:49,260 --> 01:25:52,120
- 你怎么知道？ - 我从一本书里看到的
{\fs10}- How do you know that？ - I read about it, in a book.

1179
01:25:55,200 --> 01:25:56,660
那封信他已经烧掉了
{\fs10}I'm afraid he's burned it.

1180
01:25:59,970 --> 01:26:04,670
好吧…你让我做了这么多 为何现在却要半途而废呢？
{\fs10}All right… You've had me do all the work so far, why stop now？

1181
01:26:05,310 --> 01:26:08,640
把你知道的告诉我，我去找黄金之城
{\fs10}You tell me what you know, I'll find the City of Gold,

1182
01:26:08,710 --> 01:26:11,940
只要能证明托马斯・盖茨的清白，宝藏归你
{\fs10}prove Thomas Gates' innocence, you can have the treasure.

1183
01:26:12,010 --> 01:26:13,910
- 什么？ - 我跟你一起去
{\fs10}- What？ - I'm going with you.

1184
01:26:13,980 --> 01:26:17,750
但如果别人问起黄金之城是谁发现的
{\fs10}But if anyone's gonna be credited for discovering the City of Gold,

1185
01:26:17,820 --> 01:26:19,080
答案只有一个，那就是我
{\fs10}it's going to be me.

1186
01:26:19,150 --> 01:26:22,250
但你的同伙都得留在这儿，不许带枪
{\fs10}But your partners stay here, and all the guns.

1187
01:26:22,320 --> 01:26:23,980
凭什么觉得我会同意这条件？
{\fs10}What makes you think I'd agree？

1188
01:26:24,890 --> 01:26:29,420
因为你需要这笔财宝，这一点我很清楚
{\fs10}Because you need that treasure. Believe me, I know.

1189
01:26:34,000 --> 01:26:36,230
好吧，我们按你说的做
{\fs10}All right, Gates. We'll do it your way.

1190
01:26:39,140 --> 01:26:43,010
但是相信我…带没带枪，对我都一样
{\fs10}But believe me… I don't need the guns.

1191
01:26:47,950 --> 01:26:51,750
- 哪个总统？美国总统？ - 我觉得还是不告诉你为好
{\fs10}- Which president？ The president？ - I thought it best not to tell you.

1192
01:27:05,070 --> 01:27:08,730
我还是看不到什么尊鸟的影子
{\fs10}I still don't see anything that looks like a noble bird.

1193
01:27:10,670 --> 01:27:12,640
好吧，告诉我们
{\fs10}All right. Let's have it.

1194
01:27:12,710 --> 01:27:17,140
信上写了什么？女王的信有什么线索？
{\fs10}What did the letter say？ What's the clue from Queen Victoria's letter？

1195
01:27:17,210 --> 01:27:22,510
无云之雨，出入之闾
{\fs10}"The entrance shall only be revealed under a cloudless rain. "

1196
01:27:22,580 --> 01:27:24,170
来解解看这个谜语吧
{\fs10}Figure that one out.

1197
01:27:24,250 --> 01:27:27,880
我们等下雨的时候再来？
{\fs10}So we come back when it's raining？

1198
01:27:29,890 --> 01:27:33,720
无云可能指的就是太阳
{\fs10}"Cloudless. " Could simply mean the sun.

1199
01:27:34,390 --> 01:27:37,390
在晴天的时候…下雨
{\fs10}You need a sunny day… and rain.

1200
01:27:38,770 --> 01:27:39,750
我们用水造雨
{\fs10}We need water.

1201
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:41,660
水
{\fs10}Water.

1202
01:27:52,310 --> 01:27:53,440
阿比盖尔
{\fs10}Abigail.

1203
01:27:54,610 --> 01:27:58,050
各位，水会让石头颜色变深，用水浇石头
{\fs10}Everybody, the water makes the rocks darker. Use the water.

1204
01:27:58,120 --> 01:27:59,350
艾米丽？要水么？
{\fs10}Em？ Water？

1205
01:27:59,420 --> 01:28:03,520
- 我手上的是什么？你没长眼睛啊？ - 好，好
{\fs10}- What's this in my hand？ Are you blind？ - Good, good, good.

1206
01:28:15,570 --> 01:28:18,800
太可笑了，要把水洒遍这座山？
{\fs10}This is ridiculous. Are we going to water the whole thing？

1207
01:28:28,450 --> 01:28:29,920
就是这个
{\fs10}That's it.

1208
01:28:29,980 --> 01:28:34,580
这是这个！我找到了，这边，这边！
{\fs10}Oh！ That's it. I found it. Over here！ Found it！ Over here！

1209
01:28:36,790 --> 01:28:37,920
看看
{\fs10}Look at this！

1210
01:28:39,460 --> 01:28:40,520
一只鹰
{\fs10}It's an eagle.

1211
01:28:42,500 --> 01:28:45,120
- 看啊，是一只鹰 - 还真有哎
{\fs10}- Look at that. It's an eagle. - There it is.

1212
01:28:45,570 --> 01:28:48,360
- “尊鸟有缘…” - “路在眼前”
{\fs10}- "The noble bird… " - "Will give you passage. "

1213
01:28:48,440 --> 01:28:51,930
- 现在怎么办？ - 我们应该手拉手…
{\fs10}- Uh-huh. Now what？ - We need to join hands,

1214
01:28:52,040 --> 01:28:56,910
摆出优雅高贵的姿态，走过这只鸟
{\fs10}and in a noble manner, pass over the bird.

1215
01:28:58,040 --> 01:29:01,570
- 也许它指示了方向… - 也许这鸟就会…
{\fs10}- It indicates direction… - Somehow that bird…

1216
01:29:01,650 --> 01:29:05,480
从石头上飞起，然后哑哑鸣叫…
{\fs10}…will rise from the rock and kind of caw…

1217
01:29:05,550 --> 01:29:09,780
你们要么继续胡猜瞎蒙 要么听我道出下一个线索
{\fs10}You can stand around guessing for a while, or I can give you the next clue.

1218
01:29:11,060 --> 01:29:13,960
“勇士心上，举手示降”
{\fs10}"Surrender your hand to the heart of the warrior. "

1219
01:29:15,500 --> 01:29:17,830
鹰就是勇士的标志
{\fs10}And the eagle is a symbol of the warrior.

1220
01:29:23,240 --> 01:29:25,430
本，别，等等，先别伸手
{\fs10}Ben, no. Wait, wait！ No.

1221
01:29:25,510 --> 01:29:28,200
这可能是个可怕的陷阱，快告诉他！
{\fs10}That's probably a horrible trap. Tell him！

1222
01:29:28,270 --> 01:29:29,830
这是个可怕的陷阱
{\fs10}It's a horrible trap.

1223
01:29:29,910 --> 01:29:33,540
都已经到门口了，还不试试，太可惜了
{\fs10}It would be a pity to come this far and not even try, now, wouldn't it？

1224
01:29:34,880 --> 01:29:36,250
我来吧，本
{\fs10}I'll do it, Ben.

1225
01:29:36,880 --> 01:29:37,870
没关系
{\fs10}It's OK.

1226
01:29:42,420 --> 01:29:44,290
举手示降…
{\fs10}Surrender your hand.

1227
01:30:01,310 --> 01:30:04,400
- 不好意思，我…我实在忍不住 - 你…
{\fs10}- I am sorry. I… I couldn't resist. - You！

1228
01:30:06,650 --> 01:30:10,100
摸起来好像是个门拴
{\fs10}Lt, uh… feels like a latch.

1229
01:30:19,460 --> 01:30:20,650
看看
{\fs10}Look at this.

1230
01:30:32,610 --> 01:30:35,340
好，走吧
{\fs10}All right, good. Let's go.

1231
01:31:01,670 --> 01:31:03,140
本，过来看看这个
{\fs10}Ben, look at this.

1232
01:31:04,040 --> 01:31:06,200
太漂亮了！
{\fs10}Oh, that's beautiful！

1233
01:31:09,980 --> 01:31:13,040
- 帕特里克！ - 本，那是什么？
{\fs10}- Patrick. Patrick！ - Ben, what is that？

1234
01:31:13,110 --> 01:31:16,100
像是个砝码，为保持平衡，不让门关上
{\fs10}Appears to be a counterweight to hold the door open.

1235
01:31:16,180 --> 01:31:18,280
什么声音？
{\fs10}What is that sound？

1236
01:31:18,350 --> 01:31:19,680
太迷人了
{\fs10}Fascinating.

1237
01:31:25,590 --> 01:31:26,650
本！
{\fs10}Ben！

1238
01:31:37,100 --> 01:31:38,400
对不起
{\fs10}Sorry.

1239
01:31:38,470 --> 01:31:40,060
- 还好吧？ - 不好
{\fs10}- You OK？ - No.

1240
01:31:40,540 --> 01:31:41,530
起来
{\fs10}Get up.

1241
01:31:43,380 --> 01:31:44,370
锁住了
{\fs10}It's locked.

1242
01:31:44,440 --> 01:31:49,210
- 帕特里克，瞧你都干了什么？ - 门闩自己合上了，不是我干的
{\fs10}- Patrick, what have you done？ - Some kind of a bolt. I didn't do it.

1243
01:31:49,280 --> 01:31:51,250
只有一种出去的方法了
{\fs10}Only one way out of here now.

1244
01:31:53,320 --> 01:31:54,550
往前走
{\fs10}Forward.

1245
01:32:07,100 --> 01:32:09,530
从没看到过这么多文物
{\fs10}Never seen so many relics.

1246
01:32:09,600 --> 01:32:11,700
保存如此完好
{\fs10}So beautifully preserved.

1247
01:32:15,040 --> 01:32:17,700
各位，看来我们得把这些石头搬走
{\fs10}Looks like we're going to be moving some rocks.

1248
01:32:17,780 --> 01:32:21,210
- 那后面有个通道 - 都来看看这个
{\fs10}- There's a tunnel back in through here. - Guys, look at this.

1249
01:32:24,250 --> 01:32:25,770
小金人
{\fs10}It's a little golden man.

1250
01:32:28,390 --> 01:32:33,220
看，它的身体特别小，看啊，他好像…
{\fs10}Look. It's got a tiny little torso. Look at that. It looks like…

1251
01:32:46,370 --> 01:32:48,170
- 本！ - 本！
{\fs10}- Ben！ - Ben！

1252
01:32:53,910 --> 01:32:57,180
后退，后退，你们都到另外一边去！
{\fs10}Move back！ Move back！ All of you！ Other side！

1253
01:33:00,120 --> 01:33:01,250
后退！
{\fs10}Back up！ Back up！

1254
01:33:07,630 --> 01:33:09,600
莱利，往前，往前！
{\fs10}Riley, move forward！ Move forward！

1255
01:33:10,730 --> 01:33:12,200
不，退后，退后！
{\fs10}No, back up, back up.

1256
01:33:14,370 --> 01:33:16,430
- 你要我干嘛？ - 停，停下！
{\fs10}- What you want me to do？ - Stop！ Stop！

1257
01:33:20,140 --> 01:33:23,840
我们得控制重心，这块板才不会翻
{\fs10}We have to balance our weight to even this thing out.

1258
01:33:27,010 --> 01:33:29,070
- 我们会找到他们的 - 我们怎么办？
{\fs10}- We'll find 'em. - What are we gonna do？

1259
01:33:29,150 --> 01:33:31,880
- 我有个主意，我告诉你该怎么办 - 不，我有个主意
{\fs10}Figure something out. Tell you what we're going to do.

1260
01:33:31,950 --> 01:33:34,320
不，让我来说
{\fs10}- No, I'll tell you. - No. I'll tell you！

1261
01:33:34,390 --> 01:33:37,220
不，让我来说！那里有个通道
{\fs10}No, I'll tell you！ There's that passageway.

1262
01:33:37,290 --> 01:33:41,560
你去把那些石头搬开，那肯定通向什么地方
{\fs10}You go, pull those stones out, because that leads somewhere.

1263
01:33:41,630 --> 01:33:43,750
真是一个好主意
{\fs10}That is a good idea.

1264
01:33:47,300 --> 01:33:50,430
下面没东西，只有一个黑乎乎的大洞
{\fs10}There's nothing. Just a big old black hole.

1265
01:33:54,340 --> 01:33:56,810
本，看那儿！有个梯子
{\fs10}Ben, look！ There's a ladder.

1266
01:33:56,880 --> 01:34:00,940
- 我的意思是，至少以前是个梯子 - 手电扔给我
{\fs10}- I mean, what's left of a ladder. - Toss me the light.

1267
01:34:03,450 --> 01:34:07,350
莱利，慢慢移动到那个角上，不，等下…
{\fs10}Riley. Move slowly to that corner. No！ Wait. Just…

1268
01:34:07,420 --> 01:34:10,550
- 等我往这个角上移的时候你再移 - 好
{\fs10}- As I move to this corner. - OK.

1269
01:34:12,730 --> 01:34:14,190
一次一步，很好
{\fs10}One step at a time. Good.

1270
01:34:18,560 --> 01:34:21,690
如果能让这一角升高点，我应该能够到
{\fs10}If we can raise this corner, I think I'll reach it.

1271
01:34:25,270 --> 01:34:27,500
- 停！红灯！ - 你在帮倒忙！
{\fs10}- Stop！ Red light！ - You're not helping！

1272
01:34:27,570 --> 01:34:29,630
我像你一样，也可以够得到
{\fs10}I can get up there just as easy as you.

1273
01:34:31,880 --> 01:34:32,870
先停下
{\fs10}Just stop.

1274
01:34:34,350 --> 01:34:36,510
- 你们！ - 这里是三对一
{\fs10}- Guys！ - It's three against one here.

1275
01:34:36,580 --> 01:34:40,250
我不愿最后走，既然如此 那不妨让我最先走
{\fs10}I ain't going last, and if I'm not going last, I might as well go first.

1276
01:34:41,620 --> 01:34:42,610
听着
{\fs10}Look！

1277
01:34:45,490 --> 01:34:47,080
怎么样？
{\fs10}What's it gonna be？

1278
01:34:56,540 --> 01:34:58,300
我们按你说的做
{\fs10}We'll do this your way.

1279
01:35:12,350 --> 01:35:16,220
其他人，听我数三声，然后聚拢
{\fs10}The rest of us, on my count of three, all move together.

1280
01:35:16,290 --> 01:35:17,780
一次一步
{\fs10}One step at a time.

1281
01:35:18,620 --> 01:35:21,650
一，二，三
{\fs10}One, two, three.

1282
01:35:40,980 --> 01:35:42,610
- 准备好了？ - 走
{\fs10}- You ready？ - Go.

1283
01:36:16,480 --> 01:36:18,470
米奇，你看到什么了？
{\fs10}Mitch, what do you see？

1284
01:36:19,790 --> 01:36:21,340
是出去的路吗？
{\fs10}Is there a way out？

1285
01:36:22,960 --> 01:36:24,480
上面是什么，米奇？
{\fs10}What's up there, Mitch？

1286
01:36:36,340 --> 01:36:37,500
艾米丽？
{\fs10}Em？

1287
01:36:37,570 --> 01:36:43,010
- 你还好吗？ - 向我保证，他会没事的
{\fs10}- Are you all right？ - Just promise me he's gonna be OK.

1288
01:36:47,650 --> 01:36:48,740
好
{\fs10}All right.

1289
01:36:50,550 --> 01:36:51,680
我们走
{\fs10}Let's go.

1290
01:36:52,690 --> 01:36:55,150
米奇！快回答！
{\fs10}Mitch！ Come on！

1291
01:36:55,920 --> 01:36:58,620
- 我刚才算过了… - 我知道
{\fs10}- I've been doing the math here, and… - I know.

1292
01:36:59,060 --> 01:37:01,490
我们得留一个人在这儿
{\fs10}We're gonna have to leave one person behind.

1293
01:37:01,560 --> 01:37:03,690
答应我，你们会回来找我
{\fs10}Promise you'll come back for me.

1294
01:37:03,760 --> 01:37:05,490
我也会算啊
{\fs10}I can do the math too.

1295
01:37:06,900 --> 01:37:09,560
- 那下一个该你上了 - 我最后走
{\fs10}- That makes you next. - I'll go last.

1296
01:37:11,270 --> 01:37:15,760
“不，我们会想个其它办法的” “我们需要你，求你了，莱利”
{\fs10}"No, we'll figure something else out. " "We need you there. Please, Riley. "

1297
01:37:17,510 --> 01:37:18,670
我开玩笑，你们走吧
{\fs10}I'm just kidding. Go.

1298
01:37:19,180 --> 01:37:20,740
好…
{\fs10}OK…

1299
01:37:49,680 --> 01:37:54,340
- 一…二…三！ - 走！
{\fs10}- One… two… three！ - Go！

1300
01:38:01,490 --> 01:38:03,580
- 你干了什么？ - 什么也没干
{\fs10}- What are you doing？ - Nothing.

1301
01:38:09,160 --> 01:38:10,190
我抓不到
{\fs10}I can't get it.

1302
01:38:17,240 --> 01:38:19,230
走！现在就走！快！
{\fs10}Just go！ Go now！ Go！

1303
01:38:21,740 --> 01:38:23,610
- 好，准备好了？ - 走！
{\fs10}- All right, ready？ - Now！

1304
01:38:25,950 --> 01:38:27,710
莱利！ 抓紧了！
{\fs10}Riley！ Hang on！

1305
01:38:30,720 --> 01:38:35,240
嘿，米奇，那雕像 本，我们发现了个金雕像
{\fs10}OK. Mitch, the idol. OK, Ben. We found a gold idol here！

1306
01:38:35,320 --> 01:38:38,020
我们可以用雕像来平衡你的重量
{\fs10}We can roll it over to offset your weight！

1307
01:38:38,090 --> 01:38:39,460
那就快点！
{\fs10}Then roll it！

1308
01:38:42,760 --> 01:38:43,750
来了！
{\fs10}Here it comes！

1309
01:38:52,610 --> 01:38:54,000
快，本！
{\fs10}Come on, Ben！

1310
01:38:56,880 --> 01:38:58,610
来，抓住我的手
{\fs10}Here！ Give me your hand！

1311
01:39:01,010 --> 01:39:02,500
本！
{\fs10}Ben！

1312
01:39:03,720 --> 01:39:04,770
谢谢，莱利
{\fs10}Thanks, Riley.

1313
01:39:08,050 --> 01:39:09,920
在我见义勇为的时候为啥没有女孩旁观呢？
{\fs10}Why couldn't a girl see me do that？

1314
01:39:13,930 --> 01:39:17,730
- 你还好吗？ - 没事了，你安全了
{\fs10}- You all right？ - You're OK. You're OK. You're OK.

1315
01:39:20,030 --> 01:39:22,230
那么…往前走吧
{\fs10}So… forward.

1316
01:39:25,770 --> 01:39:28,930
这是什么？
{\fs10}What is this？

1317
01:39:39,350 --> 01:39:41,180
把你的灯放在这里
{\fs10}Put your light over there.

1318
01:39:44,160 --> 01:39:45,620
你在干什么？
{\fs10}What are you doing？

1319
01:40:11,680 --> 01:40:14,150
我什么也看不到！是不是到了？
{\fs10}I can't see anything！ Is this it？

1320
01:40:19,660 --> 01:40:20,650
是油！
{\fs10}It's oil！

1321
01:40:59,770 --> 01:41:03,170
是死路！没有出路！
{\fs10}It's a dead end！ There's no way out！

1322
01:41:03,840 --> 01:41:05,300
我们得折回去！
{\fs10}We have to turn back！

1323
01:41:14,910 --> 01:41:16,240
好
{\fs10}OK.

1324
01:41:18,850 --> 01:41:21,840
不不，帕特里克，这太疯狂了
{\fs10}No. No, Patrick, this is crazy.

1325
01:41:24,720 --> 01:41:25,710
好了
{\fs10}OK.

1326
01:41:30,860 --> 01:41:32,090
成功了
{\fs10}I got it！

1327
01:41:34,300 --> 01:41:36,860
抓住你了！抓住你了！
{\fs10}I got you！ I got you！

1328
01:42:05,760 --> 01:42:07,320
不能再往前了
{\fs10}There's no forward！

1329
01:42:10,340 --> 01:42:12,530
不是往前，是往下！
{\fs10}It's not forward, it's down！

1330
01:42:13,510 --> 01:42:18,030
这些水一定从某处排出去 不然就会淹满这里
{\fs10}All this water has to go out somewhere. Otherwise, it'd be filled up.

1331
01:42:28,420 --> 01:42:30,410
来帮我推这个转盘！
{\fs10}Help me turn this wheel！

1332
01:43:03,690 --> 01:43:05,550
水是往下流的
{\fs10}The water's going down.

1333
01:43:55,670 --> 01:43:57,370
那些是…艾米丽
{\fs10}It is… Em.

1334
01:43:58,480 --> 01:44:00,470
艾米丽，艾米丽
{\fs10}Em. Em.

1335
01:44:06,690 --> 01:44:08,520
本！
{\fs10}Ben！ Hey！

1336
01:44:08,590 --> 01:44:12,890
爸爸！我们找到了！
{\fs10}Dad！ We found it！

1337
01:44:13,260 --> 01:44:16,820
- 托马斯说得没错！ - 不，是你说得没错
{\fs10}- Thomas was right！ - No, you were right！

1338
01:44:22,200 --> 01:44:25,470
对不起，我玷污了你先祖的美名
{\fs10}Sorry I smeared your great-great granddaddy's good name.

1339
01:44:25,540 --> 01:44:28,100
但这可能是唯一能让你上钩的方法
{\fs10}Seemed like the only way to get you in on the hunt.

1340
01:44:28,170 --> 01:44:32,940
这机会能让威尔金森家族留名青史
{\fs10}But this was a chance for the Wilkinson family to make its mark on history,

1341
01:44:33,010 --> 01:44:36,950
发现黄金之城，并被后世铭记
{\fs10}to find the City of Gold, to be remembered.

1342
01:45:07,750 --> 01:45:11,080
刚才发生什么了？你爸爸担心死了
{\fs10}What happened to you？ Your father was worried sick about you.

1343
01:45:11,150 --> 01:45:13,520
她差点疯掉
{\fs10}She was frantic. She was frantic.

1344
01:45:14,520 --> 01:45:17,920
爸爸，来的路上，你有没有看到…
{\fs10}Dad, coming through, did you happen to see？

1345
01:45:17,990 --> 01:45:21,930
住手，你有看到可以出去的岔路吗？
{\fs10}Stop it. Coming through, did you see any branches that could lead out？

1346
01:45:21,990 --> 01:45:25,990
没，都堵住了，连门口都回不去
{\fs10}No, it's all blocked. You can't even get back to the big, round stone door.

1347
01:45:26,500 --> 01:45:28,020
你母亲去干什么
{\fs10}Where's your mother going？

1348
01:45:30,770 --> 01:45:33,970
亲爱的，亲爱的，看看这个
{\fs10}Sweetheart. Sweetheart. Have a look at this.

1349
01:45:34,040 --> 01:45:35,130
- 什么？ - 看啊
{\fs10}- What？ - Look.

1350
01:45:35,210 --> 01:45:37,610
有了这个，就能解读奥尔麦克的文字
{\fs10}This is gonna unlock the Olmec language.

1351
01:45:37,680 --> 01:45:41,310
前哥伦布时期的美洲历史将变得豁然开朗
{\fs10}It's gonna give us incredible insight into pre-Columbian history.

1352
01:45:43,280 --> 01:45:45,040
艾米丽
{\fs10}Em？

1353
01:45:45,120 --> 01:45:47,710
- 开心吗？ - 嗯，开心
{\fs10}- You happy？ - Oh, yeah.

1354
01:45:48,690 --> 01:45:51,680
- 本，来看这个，来啊！ - 就是这个
{\fs10}- Ben！ Look at this！ Look！ - Oh, yeah.

1355
01:45:52,220 --> 01:45:55,060
这是他们割喉取心{\fs12}（祭神）{\fs18}的地方
{\fs10}That's where they slit the throat, cut the heart out.

1356
01:46:12,480 --> 01:46:15,470
- 什么声音？ - 听
{\fs10}- What was that？ - Listen.

1357
01:46:41,610 --> 01:46:45,270
我要找个出口，所有的门都堵上了
{\fs10}I tried to find a way out. All those portals are blocked off！

1358
01:46:45,340 --> 01:46:48,800
这些水总要从某个地方出去，我们会找到的
{\fs10}I'm telling you, all this water goes out somewhere. We'll find it.

1359
01:46:56,320 --> 01:46:58,220
本，水往那儿流
{\fs10}Ben, there's a current！

1360
01:46:58,660 --> 01:47:01,720
跟着找！这里肯定有个中央排水口
{\fs10}Follow it！ There's got to be a central drain！

1361
01:47:01,790 --> 01:47:03,890
就在我们脚下，就这儿！
{\fs10}It's under us. Right here！

1362
01:47:13,140 --> 01:47:14,130
快！
{\fs10}Come on！

1363
01:47:15,570 --> 01:47:17,570
我们走！进去！
{\fs10}Let's go！ Get in there！

1364
01:47:24,620 --> 01:47:26,710
水位上升太快了！
{\fs10}The water's rising too fast！

1365
01:47:26,790 --> 01:47:29,520
只要打开那道门，就不会被水淹死！
{\fs10}Let's get that door open so we don't all drown！

1366
01:47:46,240 --> 01:47:49,400
本，水顺着斜坡下去了！是一条排水管道
{\fs10}Ben, it slopes down！ It's a drainage tunnel.

1367
01:47:49,980 --> 01:47:52,240
把门打开后，水会充满通道的
{\fs10}It fills with water when you open the door！

1368
01:47:52,340 --> 01:47:55,470
我们得找点东西顶在下面，让门开着
{\fs10}We need to find something to stick under it to keep it open！

1369
01:47:55,510 --> 01:47:58,540
不，如果一直开着，这通道就会被淹
{\fs10}No, if it's open, this tunnel will stay flooded.

1370
01:47:58,620 --> 01:48:01,310
我们必须先过去，然后把门关了
{\fs10}We've got to get to the other side and close the door.

1371
01:48:01,390 --> 01:48:03,120
帕特里克，艾米丽，走！
{\fs10}Patrick, Emily, go！

1372
01:48:08,490 --> 01:48:09,550
- 不！ - 不！
{\fs10}- No. - No！

1373
01:48:11,130 --> 01:48:12,120
不！
{\fs10}No！

1374
01:48:12,200 --> 01:48:14,960
米奇，我们得到门的另一边去！
{\fs10}Mitch, we got to be on the other side of that door！

1375
01:48:15,500 --> 01:48:17,300
除非我同意，否则谁都不准走
{\fs10}Nobody leaves unless I say so.

1376
01:48:18,770 --> 01:48:21,360
门不会自己一直开着
{\fs10}That door is not gonna stay open by itself.

1377
01:48:21,440 --> 01:48:23,670
接下去该怎么做，你我都明白
{\fs10}We both know what has to happen here.

1378
01:48:24,180 --> 01:48:27,580
为了让门开着，我们中的一个得留在后面
{\fs10}One of us keeps the door open and stays behind.

1379
01:48:29,550 --> 01:48:30,640
我投米奇一票
{\fs10}I vote Mitch.

1380
01:48:31,720 --> 01:48:33,650
这不是民主表决
{\fs10}This isn't a democracy.

1381
01:48:38,290 --> 01:48:42,250
停手！我留下！我留下好了！看着！
{\fs10}Stop！ I'll stay！ I'm staying. Look. Look！

1382
01:48:43,200 --> 01:48:45,690
看见没？我就在这儿，我留下来！
{\fs10}See？ I'm right here！ I'm staying！

1383
01:48:45,760 --> 01:48:48,490
接下去怎么走，大家听好了
{\fs10}I'll tell everybody how this is going to go.

1384
01:48:48,570 --> 01:48:52,830
你我负责把这门打开，要是谁想走在我前面
{\fs10}You and me are going to open that door. Anybody tries to leave before me,

1385
01:48:52,940 --> 01:48:55,340
我就把门放下，然后从头开始
{\fs10}I drop the door, we start this all over again！

1386
01:48:55,370 --> 01:48:59,280
有谁耍花招，就要他好看！
{\fs10}Try any funny business, I guarantee you people are going to get hurt！

1387
01:49:01,180 --> 01:49:04,670
我不会的！我向你保证，先放了她吧
{\fs10}I won't！ You have my word. Just let her go.

1388
01:49:08,720 --> 01:49:11,350
本，你不走我们也不走
{\fs10}Ben, no, we're not leaving without you.

1389
01:49:13,330 --> 01:49:14,310
阿比盖尔
{\fs10}Abigail.

1390
01:49:18,430 --> 01:49:22,160
你带我父母先走，带我父母先走
{\fs10}You make my parents leave. You make my parents leave.

1391
01:49:31,510 --> 01:49:32,770
- 不！ - 走！
{\fs10}- No！ - Let's go！

1392
01:49:33,280 --> 01:49:37,240
走吧，求求你们了！ 帕特里克，艾米丽，他是在救我们的命
{\fs10}Let's go, please！ Patrick, Emily, he's trying to save our lives.

1393
01:49:37,980 --> 01:49:39,610
快，快点
{\fs10}Please, come on.

1394
01:49:41,590 --> 01:49:42,780
推啊，本
{\fs10}Push, Ben！

1395
01:49:46,460 --> 01:49:48,390
水流太强了！
{\fs10}The current's too strong！

1396
01:49:51,630 --> 01:49:53,830
- 我准备好了！ - 靠你一个了！
{\fs10}- I'm ready！ - It's all yours！

1397
01:50:16,890 --> 01:50:18,050
妈妈！
{\fs10}Mom！

1398
01:50:18,620 --> 01:50:20,850
坚持！
{\fs10}Hang on！

1399
01:50:23,700 --> 01:50:24,960
屏住呼吸！
{\fs10}Hold your breath！

1400
01:50:36,640 --> 01:50:38,370
我们得把本弄出来
{\fs10}We got to get Ben out of there！

1401
01:50:41,410 --> 01:50:45,710
如果我卡住门，门就关不上
{\fs10}If I'm stuck in the door, it stays open,

1402
01:50:45,780 --> 01:50:48,720
两个房间都会被淹，我们全部淹死
{\fs10}both rooms fill up, and we all drown！

1403
01:50:48,790 --> 01:50:52,920
- 打开门！我来换你！ - 水流太强了！
{\fs10}- Open the door！ I'll get you out！ - The current's too strong！

1404
01:50:53,030 --> 01:50:55,550
如果我打开门，你们全都会被冲走的
{\fs10}I open the door, you'll be washed down！

1405
01:50:55,590 --> 01:50:56,960
我会让你出去的！
{\fs10}I'll get you out！

1406
01:50:57,030 --> 01:51:01,400
我发现了黄金之城！是我发现的！
{\fs10}I found the City of Gold！ I found it！

1407
01:51:01,470 --> 01:51:03,460
得让外人知道这一切！
{\fs10}And no one will ever know？

1408
01:51:03,540 --> 01:51:07,770
我们可以想办法！大家都能出去的！
{\fs10}We can figure this out！ We can all get out！

1409
01:51:07,840 --> 01:51:11,400
这不是一个谜语，本，谜语说完了！
{\fs10}It's not a puzzle！ No more puzzles, Ben！

1410
01:51:11,480 --> 01:51:14,640
要么大家一起死，要么只死我一个！
{\fs10}We're all going to die, or it could just be me！

1411
01:51:15,480 --> 01:51:18,940
- 告诉大家，是我发现的！ - 别放弃！
{\fs10}- Tell them I found it！ - Don't quit！

1412
01:51:21,450 --> 01:51:22,580
米奇！
{\fs10}Mitch！

1413
01:52:03,060 --> 01:52:04,190
谢谢！
{\fs10}Thank you.

1414
01:52:21,710 --> 01:52:25,670
- 我们还没正式介绍过，我是莱利 - 噢，你好
{\fs10}- We haven't officially met. I'm Riley. - Oh, hi.

1415
01:52:31,920 --> 01:52:34,480
长官！找你的
{\fs10}Sir！ It's for you.

1416
01:52:35,790 --> 01:52:36,780
我是萨德斯基
{\fs10}Sadusky.

1417
01:52:37,730 --> 01:52:40,530
- 我找到证据了 - 本！
{\fs10}- I have my proof. - Ben！

1418
01:52:40,930 --> 01:52:44,800
我们刚还在谈论你呢，准备自首了吗？
{\fs10}We were just talking about you. Ready to turn yourself in？

1419
01:52:44,870 --> 01:52:48,530
还没准备好，我们发现了黄金之城
{\fs10}Not quite. We found the City of Gold.

1420
01:52:48,610 --> 01:52:51,410
这跟我无关，你已经犯下了重罪
{\fs10}Doesn't matter. You still committed a federal crime.

1421
01:53:11,900 --> 01:53:14,490
停下，别敲了！
{\fs10}Stop. Stop it.

1422
01:53:15,600 --> 01:53:17,930
- 总统先生？ - 克雷格，给我一分钟
{\fs10}- Mr. President？ - Craig, give us a minute.

1423
01:53:18,000 --> 01:53:21,770
先生，据您所说，此人绑架过你
{\fs10}Sir, for your information, this is the man who kidnapped you.

1424
01:53:21,840 --> 01:53:24,600
可我记得，我们俩只是在密道里探险
{\fs10}As I recall, we were exploring a hidden tunnel,

1425
01:53:24,680 --> 01:53:28,240
身后的门突然关死了，是他把我救了出来
{\fs10}and a door closed accidentally, and this man saved my life.

1426
01:53:28,580 --> 01:53:29,770
是，先生
{\fs10}Yes, sir.

1427
01:53:31,980 --> 01:53:33,750
- 盖茨 - 先生
{\fs10}- Gates. - Sir.

1428
01:53:34,820 --> 01:53:39,380
我要把这些话记下来 历经几个世纪的探险后，就在今天
{\fs10}For the record, after centuries of exploration, on this day,

1429
01:53:39,460 --> 01:53:42,980
你给你的家族和国家带来了荣耀
{\fs10}you have brought honor to your country and your family.

1430
01:53:44,530 --> 01:53:47,460
你为国家做了杰出的贡献，我感谢你
{\fs10}You've done this country a great service. I thank you.

1431
01:53:48,000 --> 01:53:50,660
- 谢谢 - 克雷格…
{\fs10}- Thank you. - Craig.

1432
01:53:52,000 --> 01:53:56,270
我觉得你可能想看看明天的报纸头版
{\fs10}I thought you might want to take a look at tomorrow's headlines.

1433
01:53:57,840 --> 01:53:58,830
明天的？
{\fs10}Tomorrow？

1434
01:54:00,340 --> 01:54:02,830
托马斯・盖茨被追认为内战英雄

1435
01:54:07,050 --> 01:54:08,310
谢谢你，先生
{\fs10}Thank you, sir.

1436
01:54:09,290 --> 01:54:11,760
你们所有的人，包括艾米丽和帕特里克・盖茨
{\fs10}All of you, along with Emily and Patrick Gates

1437
01:54:11,820 --> 01:54:13,920
由于参与了这项发现，都会受到表彰
{\fs10}will get credit for this discovery.

1438
01:54:21,070 --> 01:54:23,430
还有米奇・威尔金森，先生
{\fs10}And Mitch Wilkinson, sir.

1439
01:54:24,340 --> 01:54:28,170
- 是吗？ - 是的，先生
{\fs10}- Is that right？ - It's true, sir.

1440
01:54:29,770 --> 01:54:32,770
本，我很好奇我请你帮的那个忙
{\fs10}Ben, I am curious about that favor I asked you.

1441
01:54:34,310 --> 01:54:36,750
47页有什么？
{\fs10}Any report regarding what's on page 47？

1442
01:54:36,820 --> 01:54:39,010
我想我帮得上忙
{\fs10}I believe I can help with that, sir.

1443
01:54:39,080 --> 01:54:42,280
- 那很好 - 人生无常，总统先生
{\fs10}- So it's good. - Life-altering, sir.

1444
01:54:45,960 --> 01:54:49,590
47页上有什么？你们在说那本书？
{\fs10}What's on page 47？ Are you talking about the Book？

1445
01:54:52,830 --> 01:54:53,960
什么书？
{\fs10}What book？

1446
01:54:55,530 --> 01:54:59,590
那东西要小心伺候…你用的是蒸馏水吗？
{\fs10}Be very careful with that. Is that distilled water you're using？

1447
01:54:59,670 --> 01:55:01,940
- 是的，女士 - 所有这些东西都登记编目了吗？
{\fs10}- Yes. - Have you catalogued all of this？

1448
01:55:02,010 --> 01:55:03,370
- 没有，女士 - 你没有？
{\fs10}- No, ma'am. - You haven't？

1449
01:55:03,440 --> 01:55:06,500
抱歉？你在编这个的目录吗？
{\fs10}Excuse me？ Excuse me, sir？ Are you cataloguing this？

1450
01:55:06,580 --> 01:55:09,880
我们买沙发时，你真该在场
{\fs10}You should've been there when we picked out our first couch.

1451
01:55:13,850 --> 01:55:15,290
对不起
{\fs10}Excuse me.

1452
01:55:15,350 --> 01:55:19,260
你就是那个…那个宝藏猎人，对吗？
{\fs10}Hey, you're that guy… The treasure hunter guy, right？

1453
01:55:19,320 --> 01:55:23,160
我不是，事实上你要找的人在那边
{\fs10}No, actually, the guy you're thinking of is somewhere over there.

1454
01:55:23,230 --> 01:55:27,670
不，你就是那作者，莱利・普尔 我是从你的书上认出你的
{\fs10}No. You're him. Riley Poole. I recognize you from your book.

1455
01:55:28,330 --> 01:55:30,320
可以为我签名吗？
{\fs10}Will you sign it？

1456
01:55:30,400 --> 01:55:31,390
好啊
{\fs10}OK.

1457
01:55:40,650 --> 01:55:41,630
谢谢
{\fs10}Thank you.

1458
01:55:42,980 --> 01:55:46,210
那么，关于茶几…
{\fs10}So, um, the tea tables…

1459
01:55:47,220 --> 01:55:50,950
哦，下周我会请人搬到你那里去的
{\fs10}Yes, I'm going to have the movers bring them to you next week.

1460
01:55:51,920 --> 01:55:53,860
我刚想说，你可以留着茶几
{\fs10}I was going to say you can keep them.

1461
01:55:54,730 --> 01:55:58,860
而且你还可以…
{\fs10}And maybe you could…

1462
01:55:58,930 --> 01:56:01,230
搬回来跟我住
{\fs10}…come and move back in with me.

